United Missions of Maxima – A Pastors Blog

Posted on February 19, 2013 by herthagajg

A Pastors Blog & Intimate Moment With A Prophet

About the use of this page:

This page is specifically for individuals and small groups who would enjoy spending intimate time as a present day prophet spends his intimate time in prayer, meditation, and devotion with our Lord Jesus Christ. Witness firsthand how the Holy Spirit speaks to him and how he responds the Spirits prompting.

We encourage our reader to respond to anything the Spirit speaks to them as they read a post so that a dialog may then occur and prayerfully through dialog both the individual and the prophet may grow spiritually, and become more acute to the promptings of the Holy Spirit. For Christ told us plainly, where two or more are gathered in my name, there I will be also.

Simply respond either through email or a post at our yahoo group @ http://groups.yahoo.com/group/intimatemomentwithaprophet or email at the group. Please also be kind to the prophets post and whoever else makes post at the group, remembering we are all brothers and sisters in the Kingdom of God. You may also join Prophet Kristian on yahoo messenger by adding him at umom2003@yahoo.com. He will be on messenger most every weekday at 7 pm Central Standard Time, other than Wednesday evenings for group discussion on the devotion of the day.

You will find below an example of a post by a present day prophet. We will also keep in files menue at the yahoo group @ http://groups.yahoo.com/group/intimatemomentwithaprophet other post throughout the year that anyone may address at any time. Just in addressing another post other than the most current one, make mention of the title of the particular post.

We will also use this page where any of our Pastors, ministers, counselors, or our Senior Chief Elder of the Mission may blog to keep our whole group abreast of the most current events, especially any specific areas our one voice may be focusing efforts in.

Please make note that the content on this page changes weekly, thus, please keep checking back for most current content in what the Holy Spirit of God may be speaking to any of our pastors, ministers, or Senior Chief Elder.

Introduction to Intimate Moment With A Prophet

Introduction to the year 2012

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 03/15/2012

Â 

I first come to you hoping and praying that you enjoyed from my last series and that you have grown spiritually and in your understanding that our God does indeed still speak to His beloved children. I hope also that you have come to the realization that when sin entered the world it separated us from God, yet He loved his creation so very much that He sent His own Son as a onetime atoning sacrifice for our many sins, as now we are indeed born into sin.

Yet, though we have now found reconciliation for our sins and have forgiveness from God for our sins, when we fall, it still separates us from God until we truly repent and receive forgiveness again. It is a continuous struggle fought out in the Spiritual realms. Sin still steals our joy, and separates, thus separates us from all the blessings God wants to bestow on us, not to mention the power and presence of the Holy Spirit of God.

I pray that you also came to an understanding through my last series that there is a large difference between being saved from our sins by the grace of God and actually having a calling and us accepting the call to discipleship. To become a true disciple one must be willing to totally abandon ourselves to the Lordship of Christ and determine to be servant to all.

As you have journeyed along with me through my last series I am certain you can tell from the tone of my voice how I do become very discouraged from time to time in the numbers I find in the churches across America today of the so little few whom I feel have made the commitment to discipleship. I am sure you can see also that I feel very strongly that the only way we will ever take America back to God, is my mentoring many within the church to discipleship. There are so many times I like so many, come to this idea that we can only succeed by sheer numbers.

I turn now my attention to where God lead me today by the power of His Spirit. I was enlightened by His Spirit and am now feeling we can truly take America back to God with just a few of truly committed to discipleship. I was lead to Judges 7:2-8.

The Enemy of Trust

Judges 7:2-8

New International Version (NIV)

Â Â Â Now the camp of Midian lay below him in the valley.

I have been leaning upon my own power and understanding lately. Perhaps if God had blessed my efforts as I would have liked Him to, in giving me millions from the multitude of professed Christians across America, we might have all felt how wonderful we all are and that we had done this great work by our own might and brilliance.

If Gideon can take on an army of thousands with just three hundred, by the power and presence of the Holy Spirit of God, He can take just a few men and women who have totally abandoned themselves to the Lordship of Christ, who become so filled with the power and presence of the Holy Spirit that they simply cannot help themselves but by sharing the Love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world. We can indeed take America back to God simply by showing the true love that our Lord has for it!

David C. McCasland has much to say along these lines in RBC Ministryâ€™s daily devotion â€œOur Daily Breadâ€? for March 8. Can be found at http://odb.org/2012/03/08/the-enemy-of-trust/

â€œMilitary commanders always want to have enough troops to accomplish their mission. Most would prefer having too many not too few,â€?

You know that Scripture tells us plainly that the battle in this life is not against flesh and blood, but fought out in the spiritual domain. Never the less, it is a very real battle, thus comparing it to military commanders is more than appropriate here. As the battled being fought out here in America is probably one of the all time greatest, and satan and his army are dug in deep, and believe me, the momentum now is in his favor. There are few within America today who will not agree that the moral fiber in this nation is now where close to where it should be. Our world is in shambles! But, it is up to us to organize the children of God into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to manâ€™s laws and denominations began dividing the Body of Christ. It is up to us to unite the true disciples of Christ!

â€œWhen Gideon recruited an army of 32,000 men to stand against those who oppressed the Israelites, the Lord told him, â€œThe people who are with you are too many for Me to give the Midianites into their hands, lest Israel claim glory for itself against Me, saying, â€˜My own hand has saved meâ€™â€? (Judg. 7:2).â€?

The Lord said; â€œI will save you, and deliver the Midianites into your handâ€? (v.7). And so it happened (vv.19-23).

In our life of faith, our resources can become the enemy of trust. God wants us to depend on Him, not our own strength, whether physical, financial, or intellectual.

When the Lord reduces our resources from â€œ32,000 to 300,â€? it is not punishment. It is preparation for Him to be glorified through our lives as we acknowledge and trust His power.

Are there a few in the Christian community who are prepared to be mentored into true disciples of Christ, to totally abandon themselves to the Kingdom of God, and to maximize their individual God given talents and resources to build up the Kingdom of God on earth as it is in Heaven? Are we prepared to trust God and depend entirely upon Him, and when He gives us the victory to acknowledge Him and to give Him all the glory?

The Maximia Disciples of Christ of the United Missions of Maxima is seeking now just a few true disciples of Christ to help us to take this once great nation back to God!

Introduction to the year 2012

A Series which the Holy Spirit Lead me in during the first part of this year:

I have just completed a series which I didnt initially intend to be a series, but for some reason it appears that the Spirit has been speaking to me along the same line for some time now. It is not actually the end of a series of Intimate Moments With A Prophet. So, for my reader to better understand this particular page I have listed from top to bottom until you come to a section entitled TAKING AMERICA BACK TO GOD from January 30, 2012 through March 3, 2012, with January 30 being the first and March 3 being the last of this particular series.

As stated I did not set out with the intentions of making this like a series. I had originally set out the first of a new year to share my intimate time I was spending in the Spirit, in prayer, and meditation and when I first began this new year the Holy Spirit was sharing with me some specific things that He wanted me to make known to my reader, one of the primary things was that God is very much alive and well today, and that He still reveals Himself to His children and still speaks to His children.

The beginning of this new year I was being lead to see how so many within the church in America today seem to speak of God almost in a past tense sort of way. At best, He is still alive and still all knowing, but He certainly no longer communicates directly with His children directly any longer, at best, we may get to know what He may want from reading His Word or perhaps having a pastor or church leader read His Word to us. Not that this is not true, for God does still speak to His children through His Word, however, He also has many other ways at His disposal to communicate with His Children.

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 01/30/2012

Prophet on the Bay

Dr. Kristian Shepard

Scripture Reading:

1 Samuel 3:10-19

New International Version (NIV)

10 The LORD came and stood there, calling as at the other times, Samuel! Samuel!

Then Samuel said, Speak, for your servant is listening.

11 And the LORD said to Samuel: See, I am about to do something in Israel that will make the ears of everyone who hears about it tingle. 12 At that time I will carry out against Eli everything I spoke against his familyfrom beginning to end. 13 For I told him that I would judge his family forever because of the sin he knew about; his sons blasphemed God, and he failed to restrain them. 14 Therefore I swore to the house of Eli, The guilt of Elis house will never be atoned for by sacrifice or offering.

15 Samuel lay down until morning and then opened the doors of the house of the LORD. He was afraid to tell Eli the vision, 16 but Eli called him and said, Samuel, my son.

Samuel answered, Here I am.

17 What was it he said to you? Eli asked. Do not hide it from me. May God deal with you, be it ever so severely, if you hide from me anything he told you. 18 So Samuel told him everything, hiding nothing from him. Then Eli said, He is the LORD; let him do what is good in his eyes.

19 The LORD was with Samuel as he grew up, and he let none of Samuels words fall to the ground.

I turn now to the Daily Devotional for January 30 of Oswald Chambers found at http://rbc.org/

Chambers begins his discourse with; God never speaks to us in startling ways, but in ways that are easy to misunderstand, and we say, “I wonder if that is Gods voice?” Isaiah said that the Lord spake to him “with a strong hand,” that is, by the pressure of circumstances. Nothing touches our lives but it is God Himself speaking. Do we discern His hand or only mere occurrence?

There are a couple of things which the Holy Spirit of God brought to my attention while in prayer and in the Spirit after reading this first paragraph of this devotion that I have highlighted in red. First and foremost; back in 1999 when my Lord first began giving to me visions and revelations, when He first began speaking to me specific things which I was to go from there and to present to first the church, and then to the masses, was the way in which He spoke to me.

There was really nothing special going on other than I had become accustomed to doing what I called Spiritual Revival Retreats basically meaning, I was at a camp I had set up, finding that the more of this world I would leave behind, the more apt the Spirit of God being present. I had done several of these over the past several weekends where several individuals and couples had attended in a study of how to be completely filled with the Holy Spirit of God. The word was getting out of some of the miracles which had taken place over these weekends, thus people had begun to get interested in attending.

In fact, there had been planned this particular weekend for six people to attend, but for whatever reason, all had cancelled. It had actually turned out to be a transitional section of my life where God had brought a girl I had been involved with in my secular days who had transitioned with me to ministry when I received my call, to show me once and for all she had not actually been called to this same ministry. She didnt even like to camp, so just the idea of her deciding to come along for this particular weekend convinced me it was a God thing.

Regardless, God spoke to me convincingly that she was not to be my wife, as He had not called her to this ministry. All of the events of this particular weekend are recorded elsewhere in archives, and even a video tape of the highlights of this weekend have been saved, as the Holy Spirit had spoken very clearly to video a portion of the weekend. If we are ever able to meet, be sure to ask me about viewing this video, as it is a very interesting video where one can witness my mouth being the mouth piece for both God and Satan, as one can witness the Spiritual warfare we all go through.

The events of this particular weekend are not important to what the Spirit was speaking to me today. The point here was the simplicity in which God spoke, and how sure I was in that it was Him who was speaking.

The second thing which the Spirit spoke to me concerning this devotion was the second highlighted portion in paragraph one; Nothing touches our lives but it is God Himself speaking. I have found this is especially true when and if we have truly totally abandoned ourselves to the Lordship of Christ. Then everyday is a romance with my Lord, as He walks with me and He talks with me, and He tells me that I am His own, and the joy we share as we tarry there, none other has ever known.

This devotion and the power and presence of the Holy Spirit takes me back to a time when I was totally abandoned to the Lordship of Christ, a time He spent considerable hours speaking to me of things I was to take to the people. I have to ask myself, where did I get off track, and why am I not there now? Did I spend too much time listening to others? Was I influenced by others? AS I proceeded with my studies, was I drawn back to the world and self? I am not saying that I do not spend much time with my Lord. Nor, am I saying He has stopped speaking to His servant. I have just simply varied off from a time where absolutely everything in my life happened for a particular reason, nothing happening in my life by chance.

Chambers discourse as it continues hints as to why;

Get into the habit of saying, “Speak, Lord,” and life will become a romance. Every time circumstances press, say, “Speak, Lord”; make time to listen. Chastening is more than a means of discipline, it is meant to get me to the place of saying, “Speak, Lord.” Recall the time when God did speak to you. Have you forgotten what He said? Was it Luke 11:13,

Luke 11:13

New International Version (NIV)

13 If you then, though you are evil, know how to give good gifts to your children, how much more will your Father in heaven give the Holy Spirit to those who ask him!

or was it 1 Thess. 5:23?

1 Thessalonians 5:23

New International Version (NIV)

23 May God himself, the God of peace, sanctify you through and through. May your whole spirit, soul and body be kept blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ?

As we listen, our ear gets acute, and, like Jesus, we shall hear God all the time.

Our Lord is always present! It is we who go astray. It is us who gets completely wrapped up in the world, that we ourselves take time away from a romance of a lifetime, that romance with our wonderful Lord Jesus Christ.

That is certainly the case with me. If my reader has spent any time at any of our websites; www.umomaxima.org or www.hoperetreatsintternational.org or spent time at our group Intimate Moment With A Prophet, then you know after my receiving many of the visions and revelations given me by God that one of the first things I was to do was to return to school. I was to enter seminary to study pastorate ministry with emphasis in Nouthetic Biblical Counseling to one day receive my ph. D so as to communicate these visions to main line denominational pastors. I was also lead back to school to get my ph. D in Mass Communications so as to be able to teach what I had done all my life before ministry, which was film making, on a collegiate level so I would not have to take funds from the ministry I had been called to live on.

I was so excited about the opportunity of attending seminary, as I was certain through seminary I would first find comfort and support of these visions and revelations I had received from God. I felt excitement, as I was certain all ministers would find sheer excitement along with me at the possibilities of uniting into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body of Christ, and that through this united effort we may together show a watching world the love Christ our Lord has for it in very practical ways, and thus taking America back to God.

Unfortunately, pastor after pastor I met with explained to me that God does not speak directly to individuals any longer. He certainly does not reveal Himself directly to an individual. I wondered then, why the Holy Scripture tells us that He reveals Himself to those who are His own, yet evidently He had chosen not to reveal Himself to these pastors I was seeing.

All I knew and had to go on, was for some strange reason my Lord had chosen to reveal Himself to me in a very real way, and in a very convincing way exactly what He had called me to, and exactly what He had planned for me then and for the rest of my life. Still, I kept returning to my thinking, why me, but more importantly, if God was really about to judge America, and it was indeed His perfect will that His people repent and unite in the One Body of Christ that Christ came to establish, and through this unity, take first the Church in America back to God, then taking America back to God, why then did not every other pastor, minister, and church leader get this.

All I knew and had to go on, was for some strange reason my Lord had chosen to reveal Himself to me in a very real way, and in a very convincing way exactly what He had called me to, and exactly what He had planned for me then and for the rest of my life. Still, I kept returning to my thinking, why me, but more importantly, if God was really about to judge America, and it was indeed His perfect will that His people repent and unite in the One Body of Christ that Christ came to establish, and through this unity, take first the Church in America back to God, then taking America back to God, why then did not every other pastor, minister, and church leader get this.

One thing I was absolutely certain of was this; the more I had abandoned myself to the Lordship of Christ, the more my Lord filled me with the power and presence of His precious Spirit. At one point in my life in ministry, I witnessed the sick healed, demon possessed individuals delivered, addicts healed completely, the mentally ill healed, relationships restored, and the list goes on and on what the power of the Holy Spirit did through an abandoned servant.

The more I abandoned myself to His Lordship, it became more and more apparent it was no longer me, but His wonderful Love for a hurting world being manifested through me. He shared with me that His Kingdom was all about relationship, relationship, relationship, first a very real, very intimate, loving eternal relationship with the person of Christ, and then this same intimate relationship with all who belong to His Kingdom, not to mention a real love for my neighbor.

He showed me how He had so blessed America over the past 200+ years because so many of our forefathers were His very own and as a majority this nation was a God fearing people who were true followers of Christ. Unfortunately, He also showed me how so many had returned to the world and self and how He was about to judge America. He actually took me to a place where I had thought I was in the Garden of Eden, such a perfect place, surrounded by His wonderful love and peace. I was only told latter it was actually America after He had totally re-vegetated the land after He had laid it wasted after His judgment on her if America does not repent and turn back to God.

He shared with me that the only way America would come to such a repentance was if the Church in America was brought back to God, by showing a watching world the true unity of the Body of Christ and the true love that Christ had for a hurting world manifested through this unity of true followers of Christ in very practical ways. We were to become the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body.

He shared with me many of the stories of millions of Americans going to the Church in todays culture seeking truth, and seeking our precious Lord only to find they were first judged by the church, condemned by the church, and then crucified by the church just after Wednesday night fellowship dinner. He showed me how so many churches in America today were so much more concerned with a denominations doctrine, a method, a cause, so many other things as opposed to having concern in building up the Kingdom of God.

I thought, oh my God! Who am I to address such issues? Here I am just beginning my study in ministry, and there are so many pastors out there who have studied for so many years. Are they not so much more qualified than I to take on such a crusade for Christ?

At any rate, I started out strong in sharing many of the visions and revelations my Lord had shared with me that I was to take to the people, as I prodded along with my studies. As mentioned I have witnessed so many healings and people come to know our Lord Jesus as their own Lord and Savior, but have failed miserably in putting together this unity. I could go on and on in the many road blocks Satan has placed before me, but time will not allow it here. This unity has been called everything down to a cult by the religious leaders of our day. I just never understood how one so learned in the Scripture could identify us as such, simply because I have been lead by the Holy Spirit of God to call us all into a unified love. Isnt that what the church is supposed to be?

As time passed, I guess over time I have listened too much to the satanic forces around me, and just do not have the zeal I once did. I did finish one of my ph.ds, and still studying my ph. D in pastorate ministry, and I continue by Gods grace to build this unity of true followers, praying continually that we are able to take America back to God, if for no other reason, to give more time that some more may be saved before our Lords return.

Anyway, todays devotion was an outlet for the Holy Spirit to once again speak to me concerning the visions He had already given me and to perhaps re-kindle the fire I once had. After spending time in the Spirit today I felt compelled to once again share at least a portion of the vision. I was lead to once again proclaim boldly the vision given me by God, to tell my Eli the church in America today.

Chambers continues in his discourse;

Shall I tell my “Eli” what God has shown to me? That is where the dilemma of obedience comes in. We disobey God by becoming amateur providences I must shield “Eli,” the best people we know. God did not tell Samuel to tell Eli; he had to decide that for himself. Gods call to you may hurt your “Eli;” but if you try to prevent the suffering in another life, it will prove an obstruction between your soul and God. It is at your own peril that you prevent the cutting off of the right hand or the plucking out of the eye.

Never ask the advice of another about anything God makes you decide before Him. If you ask advice, you will nearly always side with Satan. “Immediately I conferred not with flesh and blood.”

In closing I feel it necessary to share once again at least the basics of the Vision of Maxima. I first turn to another Scripture. 1 Corinthians 1: 10-17, as I feel we should always be able to back up anything we find ourselves believing it is of God, to support with Holy Scripture.

A Church Divided Over Leaders”

10 I appeal to you, brothers and sisters, in the name of our Lord Jesus Christ, that all of you agree with one another in what you say and that there be no divisions among you, but that you be perfectly united in mind and thought. 11 My brothers and sisters, some from Chloes household have informed me that there are quarrels among you. 12 What I mean is this: One of you says, I follow Paul; another, I follow Apollos; another, I follow Cephas ; still another, I follow Christ.

13 Is Christ divided? Was Paul crucified for you? Were you baptized in the name of Paul? 14 I thank God that I did not baptize any of you except Crispus and Gaius, 15 so no one can say that you were baptized in my name. 16 (Yes, I also baptized the household of Stephanas; beyond that, I dont remember if I baptized anyone else.) 17 For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospelnot with wisdom and eloquence, lest the cross of Christ be emptied of its power.

Was Paul crucified for you? Were you baptized in the name of Paul? 14 I thank God that I did not baptize any of you except Crispus and Gaius, 15 so no one can say that you were baptized in my name. 16 (Yes, I also baptized the household of Stephanas; beyond that, I dont remember if I baptized anyone else.) 17 For Christ did not send me to baptize, but to preach the gospelnot with wisdom and eloquence, lest the cross of Christ be emptied of its power.

Is Christ divided? Should His Body be divided? One of the cornerstones of the vision of Maxima is all the true followers of Christ be united into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be, so that a watching world may witness exactly what unity means.

Through this unity, share the real love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world through practical ways. To first share in a real love for one another, then out to the watching world. We are to be forgiving of one another, not continually bickering with one another. We are to share the same grace our Lord shared with us to one another, for we know all have sinned and fallen short of the glory of God.

We are to enter into covenant relationship with our Lord Jesus and one another under the two greatest commands as well as the last our Lord gave to us before returning to sit at the right hand of God, which was to go and make disciples of all the nations. We feel strongly that before we can adequately make disciples of all the nations, we may fist consider making disciples of our own.

In a nut shell, if one can imagine two films joined as one, they may begin to get a glimpse of the Vision of Maxima. The two films are Courageous and Pay it Forward.

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 02/02/2012

Scripture Reading is 1 Corinthians 9:7-16

New International Version (NIV)

7 Who serves as a soldier at his own expense? Who plants a vineyard and does not eat its grapes? Who tends a flock and does not drink the milk? 8 Do I say this merely on human authority? Doesnt the Law say the same thing? 9 For it is written in the Law of Moses: Do not muzzle an ox while it is treading out the grain.

Is it about oxen that God is concerned? 10 Surely he says this for us, doesnt he? Yes, this was written for us, because whoever plows and threshes should be able to do so in the hope of sharing in the harvest. 11If we have sown spiritual seed among you, is it too much if we reap a material harvest from you? 12 If others have this right of support from you, shouldnt we have it all the more?

But we did not use this right. On the contrary, we put up with anything rather than hinder the gospel of Christ.

13 Dont you know that those who serve in the temple get their food from the temple, and that those who serve at the altar share in what is offered on the altar? 14 In the same way, the Lord has commanded that those who preach the gospel should receive their living from the gospel.

15 But I have not used any of these rights. And I am not writing this in the hope that you will do such things for me, for I would rather die than allow anyone to deprive me of this boast. 16For when I preach the gospel, I cannot boast, since I am compelled to preach. Woe to me if I do not preach the gospel!

If one has known me very long, and has followed any of my teachings dealing with the visions and revelations given me by God to take to the people, I am certain you have heard many of my discourses concerning Salvation VS Discipleship or on subjects such as Can one be saved without becoming a disciple. I believe todays devotional from Oswald Chambers My Utmost for His Highest February 2 addresses this topic better than I have seen it addressed elsewhere. I have entered the whole devotion of Chambers here and will highlight in blue what I feel the Spirit is speaking directly.

Beware of refusing to hear the call of God. Everyone who is saved is called to testify to the fact of his salvation. That, however, is not the same as the call to preach, but is merely an illustration which can be used in preaching. In this verse, Paul was referring to the stinging pains produced in him by the compelling force of the call to preach the gospel. Never try to apply what Paul said regarding the call to preach to those souls who are being called to God for salvation.

There is nothing easier than getting saved, because it is solely Gods sovereign work Look to Me, and be saved . . . (Isaiah 45:22). Our Lord never requires the same conditions for discipleship that he requires for salvation. We are condemned to salvation through the Cross of Christ. But discipleship has an option with it-If anyone . . . (Luke 14:26).

Pauls words have to do with our being made servants of Jesus Christ, and our permission is never asked as to what we will do or where we will go. God makes us as broken bread and poured-out wine to please Himself. To be separated to the gospel means being able to hear the call of God (Romans 1:1). Once someone begins to hear that call, a suffering worthy of the name of Christ is produced. Suddenly, every ambition, every desire of life, and every outlook is completely blotted out and extinguished. Only one thing remains . . . separated to the gospel. . . . Woe be to the soul who tries to head in any other direction once that call has come to him. The Bible Training College exists so that each of you may know whether or not God has a man or woman here who truly cares about proclaiming His gospel and to see if God grips you for this purpose. Beware of competing calls once the call of God grips you.

At the United Missions of Maxima, this is exactly what we are seeking. We are not seeking simply saved souls, but those who have received the call to be disciples of Christ! We are seeking diligently those who have been lead by the Holy Spirit to become disciples of Christ and to unite into the one mind and one accord we were meant to be, one Body of Christ, One Lord, One Spirit in an all out effort to Maximize our individual God given talents and resources to build up the Kingdom of God, on earth as it is in Heaven, by sharing the Love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world through very practical ways, thus somehow by Gods grace to take America back to God!

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 02/07/2012

Are You Ready to be A Disciple for Christ?

My Lord came and stood by me and asked, Where are my disciples in the Church in America today?

I said, here I am Lord! Send me! Where shall I go for you and what shall I do?

Paul told Timothy in 2 Timothy 4:6;

I am already being poured out as a drink offering . . .

He says to the Church in Philippians 2:17;

17 But even if I am being poured out like a drink offering on the sacrifice and service coming from your faith, I am glad and rejoice with all of you.

Oswald Chambers ask in his devotional My Utmost for His Highestfor February 5;

Are you willing to sacrifice yourself for the work of another believerto pour out your life sacrificially for the ministry and faith of others? Or do you say, I am not willing to be poured out right now, and I dont want God to tell me how to serve Him. I want to choose the place of my own sacrifice. And I want to have certain people watching me and saying, Well done.

I said to my Lord, my Lord and my God, seems most in the churches across America today, perhaps across the globe, are these kind of individuals, more concerned with receiving their praise and rewards from man other than being true disciples of you Lord! Chambers continues his discourse in the same devotional;

It is one thing to follow Gods way of service if you are regarded as a hero, but quite another thing if the road marked out for you by God requires becoming a doormat under other peoples feet. Gods purpose may be to teach you to say, I know how to be abased . . . (Philippians 4:12). Are you ready to be sacrificed like that?

Perhaps we should read the scripture quoted above in a larger context, say beginning with verse one.

2 Timothy 4:1-6

New International Version (NIV)

2 Timothy 4

1 In the presence of God and of Christ Jesus, who will judge the living and the dead, and in view of his appearing and his kingdom, I give you this charge: 2 Preach the word; be prepared in season and out of season; correct, rebuke and encouragewith great patience and careful instruction. 3For the time will come when people will not put up with sound doctrine. Instead, to suit their own desires, they will gather around them a great number of teachers to say what their itching ears want to hear. 4 They will turn their ears away from the truth and turn aside to myths. 5 But you, keep your head in all situations, endure hardship, do the work of an evangelist, discharge all the duties of your ministry.

6 For I am already being poured out like a drink offering, and the time for my departure is near.”

My Lord and my God, those times have arrived!

Yes, yes, Our dear servant The Spirit spoke to me. This is why you are in the position you are in now. When we blessed you so, once you had been transformed by my power and you had become a true disciple, we allowed you the luxury of returning to school to get your degrees, but it was to bring glory to God, not yourself, so that you would have the worldly qualifications to take our message to first the church and then to all the people.

You instead, got caught back up into the world. You did not remain true to your calling. You allowed Our enemy to distract you. Now you must repent and re-learn once again what We expect from our true disciples so that you may then carry out your purpose, the calling you so eagerly accepted several years ago. You must do this so that you once again will realize what a true disciple is, as you cannot teach others, or disciple others before you yourself have learned what a true disciple is.

Have you forgotten how We spent so much time with you showing you how We are more concerned with those within the church in America today actually doing what they already know to do rather than trying to make disciples of all the nations before they themselves know how to act as a true disciple.

You must so totally abandon yourself to US, that our power may come through you so that the watching world may know with certainty that you are Our messenger, and that the message is that those Americans throughout the churches in America must first repent and return to God, and that then and only then will we be in them so powerfully that they are able to take America back for Us. Then you may speak again boldly, for only then will we so fill you with Our power to enable you to do so. You must become a disciple of Christ once again.

I beg of you your pardon Lord! You are so right, I have sinnedagainst you, please forgive me. I do now totally abandon myself to your Lordship and commit to follow you to the ends of the world! I now make room by emptying myself of self making room for you to completely fill me with the power and presence of your Holy Spirit.

I am now once again Ready To Be Poured Out As an Offering

Is my reader ready to be a true disciple of Christ? Is my reader ready to unite with me in what may very well be the last great awakening, the last real crusade for Christ, and by this unity take America back to God?

Chambers continues his discourse into the next days devotional, February 6;

Are you ready to be poured out as an offering? It is an act of your will, not your emotions. Tell God you are ready to be offered as a sacrifice for Him. Then accept the consequences as they come, without any complaints, in spite of what God may send your way. God sends you through a crisis in private, where no other person can help you

From the outside your life may appear to be the same, but the difference is taking place in your will. Once you have experienced the crisis in your will, you will take no thought of the cost when it begins to affect you externally. If you dont deal with God on the level of your will first, the result will be only to arouse sympathy for yourself

Bind the sacrifice with cords to the horns of the altar (Psalm 118:27). You must be willing to be placed on the altar and go through the fire; willing to experience what the altar represents-burning, purification, and separation for only one purpose-the elimination of every desire and affection not grounded in or directed toward God

But you dont eliminate it, God does see to it that you dont wallow in self-pity once the fire begins. After you have gone through the fire, there will be nothing that will be able to trouble or depress you. When another crisis arises, you will realize that things cannot touch you as they used to do

Tell God you are ready to be poured out as an offering, and God will prove Himself to be all you ever dreamed He would be.

Are you ready to begin such a journey with our precious Lord? Are you ready for the romance of a lifetime? Are you prepared to be not just a saved soul, but a disciple of Christ our Lord?

Are you ready to join me now in this unity of the Body of Christ, in not only preaching about the wonderful love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world, but actually sharing this immense love for a hurting world in very practical ways? Are we ready to take this once God fearing, great nation back to God?

Remember, we are living for eternity, and not for this world only. We do not seek our rewards here for simply the here and now, but seek rather eternal rewards. In fact God spoke to me concerning just that in todays devotional in RBCs Ministrys Our Daily Bread The Scripture was Matthew 6:1-6,16-18

Giving to the Needy

1 Be careful not to practice your righteousness in front of others to be seen by them. If you do, you will have no reward from your Father in heaven.

2 So when you give to the needy, do not announce it with trumpets, as the hypocrites do in the synagogues and on the streets, to be honored by others. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full. 3 But when you give to the needy, do not let your left hand know what your right hand is doing, 4 so that your giving may be in secret. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.

Prayer

5 And when you pray, do not be like the hypocrites, for they love to pray standing in the synagogues and on the street corners to be seen by others. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full. 6 But when you pray, go into your room, close the door and pray to your Father, who is unseen. Then your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.

Fasting

16 When you fast, do not look somber as the hypocrites do, for they disfigure their faces to show others they are fasting. Truly I tell you, they have received their reward in full. 17 But when you fast, put oil on your head and wash your face, 18 so that it will not be obvious to others that you are fasting, but only to your Father, who is unseen; and your Father, who sees what is done in secret, will reward you.

To quote Our Daily Bread after the author speaks about how many companies in America today give rewards for loyal shopping with them;

God has a rewards program as well. Jesus often spoke of His desire to reward us for loyally serving Him. When we are persecuted for His sake, for example, He says to rejoice . . . for great is your reward in heaven (Matt. 5:12). In contrast to the Pharisees pious habit of giving, praying, and fasting in public, Jesus instructed us to do these things privately, because your Father who sees in secret will Himself reward you openly (6:4,6,18). When it comes to living for Jesus, faithfulness never ultimately puts your life in a deficit position, regardless of what it costs

But we dont serve Jesus for the rewards. When He died for us on the cross, He did far more for us than we deserve. Loyalty to Him is an act of worship that expresses our loving gratitude for His love toward us. In return, He delights to encourage us with the assurance that ultimately His rewards will outweigh whatever we have given up for Him.

Live for Jesusregardless of the cost.

What is done for Christ in this life
will be rewarded in the life to come.

The Cost of Sanctification

1 Thessalonians 5:16-24

New International Version (NIV)

16 Rejoice always, 17 pray continually, 18 give thanks in all circumstances; for this is Gods will for you in Christ Jesus.

19Do not quench the Spirit. 20Do not treat prophecies with contempt 21 but test them all; hold on to what is good, 22 reject every kind of evil.

23May God himself, the God of peace, sanctify you through and through. May your whole spirit, soul and body be kept blameless at the coming of our Lord Jesus Christ. 24 The one who calls you is faithful, and he will do it.

In Oswald Chambers daily devotional, My Utmost for His Highest for todays date, Chambers says; We take the word sanctification much too lightly. Are we prepared to pay the cost of sanctification?

Perhaps this is a primary reason many in the churches across our land today are reluctant in becoming true disciples of Christ, as they are also reluctant in allowing the Holy Spirit of God to come in and completely sanctify them. Chambers continues his discourse;

Sanctification means to be intensely focused on Gods point of view. It means to secure and to keep all the strength of our body, soul, and spirit for Gods purpose alone. Are we really prepared for God to perform in us everything for which He separated us? And after He has done His work, are we then prepared to separate ourselves to God just as Jesus did? The reason some of us have not entered into the experience of sanctification is that we have not realized the meaning of sanctification from Gods perspective.

Sanctification means being made one with Jesus so that the nature that controlled Him will control us. Are we really prepared for what that will cost? It will cost absolutely everything in us which is not of God

Are we prepared to be caught up into the full meaning of Pauls prayer in this verse? Are we prepared to say, Lord, make me, a sinner saved by grace, as holy as You can? Jesus prayed that we might be one with Him, just as He is one with the Father (seeJohn 17:21-23). The resounding evidence of the Holy Spirit in a persons life is the unmistakable family likeness to Jesus Christ, and the freedom from everything which is not like Him. Are we prepared to set ourselves apart for the Holy Spirits work in us?

The people simply have too many lust in competition with Me!

It is time we made a covenant with our eyes as Job did in Job 31:1-4;

1 I made a covenant with my eyes
not to look lustfully at a young woman.

2 For what is our lot from God above,
our heritage from the Almighty on high?
3 Is it not ruin for the wicked,
disaster for those who do wrong?
4 Does he not see my ways
and count my every step?

There is of course many kinds of lust, and in todays culture there are literally thousands of temptations which compete with the promptings of the Holy Spirit of God.

More Scripture for today:

1 Thessalonians 4:1-8

New International Version (NIV)

1 Thessalonians 4

Living to Please God

1 As for other matters, brothers and sisters, we instructed you how to live in order to please God, as in fact you are living. Now we ask you and urge you in the Lord Jesus to do this more and more. 2 For you know what instructions we gave you by the authority of the Lord Jesus.

3It is Gods will that you should be sanctified: that you should avoid sexual immorality; 4 that each of you should learn to control your own bodyin a way that is holy and honorable, 5 not in passionate lust like the pagans, who do not know God; 6 and that in this matter no one should wrong or take advantage of a brother or sister. The Lord will punish all those who commit such sins, as we told you and warned you before. 7 For God did not call us to be impure, but to live a holy life. 8 Therefore, anyone who rejects this instruction does not reject a human being but God, the very God who gives you his Holy Spirit.

Jennifer Benson Schuldt tells of a friend of hers in RBCs Devotional today in their Our Daily Bread devotional;

Our friend is a computer techie. One night when our family was at his house, I noticed a verse taped to his monitor: I have made a covenant with my eyes (Job 31:1)

Like many of us, Job had promised himself to stay free of lust. Reflecting on that oath, he said, Does [God] not see my ways, and count all my steps? (v.4). The Bible assures us that God does (Heb. 4:13), and that we are accountable to Him

While some want to debate the boundaries of morality, the Bible says, Whoever looks at a woman to lust for her has already committed adultery with her in his heart (Matt. 5:28).

If you have made a covenant with your eyes, consider how Scripture might help you keep this pledge. Post a verse on your computer screen, television, or the dashboard of your car, and remember, God did not call us to uncleanness but to holiness (1 Thess. 4:7).

When lustful thoughts assail your mind
To play with immorality,
Remember that Gods will for you
Is holiness and purity. Sper

A look that lingers can lead to lust.

Matthew 23:23-30

New International Version (NIV)

23Woe to you, teachers of the law and Pharisees, you hypocrites! You give a tenth of your spicesmint, dill and cumin. Are You Listening to God?

They said to Moses, You speak with us, and we will hear; but let not God speak with us, lest we die `Exodus 20:19

Chambers in his devotional My Utmost for His Highest for day February 12 says;

We dont consciously and deliberately disobey God we simply dont listen to Him. God has given His commands to us, but we pay no attention to them not because of willful disobedience, but because we do not truly love and respect Him. If you love Me, keep My commandments (John 14:15). Once we realize we have constantly been showing disrespect to God, we will be filled with shame and humiliation for ignoring Him

You speak with us, . . . but let not God speak with us . . . . We show how little love we have for God by preferring to listen to His servants rather than to Him Why are we so terrified for God to speak to us? It is because we know that when God speaks we must either do what He asks or tell Him we will not obey. But if it is simply one of Gods servants speaking to us, we feel obedience is optional, not imperative. We respond by saying, Well, thats only your own idea, even though I dont deny that what you said is probably Gods truth.

Am I constantly humiliating God by ignoring Him, while He lovingly continues to treat me as His child?

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 02/13/2012

Prophet on the Bay

Dr. Kristian Shepard

You know, over the years I have questioned why so many within the churches across America today do not do what they already know to do. I have even gone as far as to question whether or not some are even reading the same scripture as I read.

When I have approached pastors and church leaders since my Lord began speaking directly to me, sharing with me so many visions and revelations, walking and talking with me in my daily journey, so many have expressed to me something along the lines; that God no longer speaks directly to anyone any longer, that He may speak through His Word, etc but any direct communication is not heard of. I must simply say, this is very interesting how God, the creator of this universe and everything in it, who has spoken even through an ass, spoke through prophets, and many other ways, has for some reason just simply stopped speaking to mankind, and if He has, why in the world would He single me out, and only speak to me directly.

Another question which comes to my mind is why God would say in Scripture that He would reveal Himself to those who belonged to Him, in fact Christ our Lord even said, they would come and reside within us. Have they come to simply reside and not communicate?

Oswald Chambers touches perhaps on this subject in todays devotional in his devotional classic, My Utmost for His Highest;

Because I have listened definitely to one thing from God, it does not follow that I will listen to everything He says. The way in which I show God that I neither love nor respect Him is by the obtuseness of my heart and mind towards what He says. If I love my friend, I intuitively detect what he wants, and Jesus says, “Ye are My friends.” Have I disobeyed some command of my Lords this week? If I had realized that it was a command of Jesus, I would not consciously have disobeyed it; but most of us show such disrespect to God that we do not even hear what He says, He might never have spoken.

Perhaps the above referenced Scripture gives us some insight as to why so many within the Churches across America do not hear from God, perhaps it is the fact they are not listening. Perhaps they have not been trained in how to listen to God, as I have found that God speaks to us in so many different ways. This is an important that anyone who joins Maxima is thoroughly trained in how to listen for God. Perhaps it is simply they have other things in life they are more in love with than our Lord Jesus? As Chambers said in the preceding paragraph; If I love my friend, I intuitively detect what he wants, and Jesus says, “Ye are My friends.”

Chambers continues his discourse;

The destiny of my spiritual life is such identification with Jesus Christ that I always hear God, and I know that God always hears me (John 11:41). If I am united with Jesus Christ, I hear God, by the devotion of hearing all the time. A lily, or a tree, or a servant of God, may convey

Gods message to me. What hinders me from hearing is that I am taken up with other things. It is not that I will not hear God, but I am not devoted in the right place. I am devoted to things, to service, to convictions, and God may say what He likes but I do not hear Him. The child attitude is always, “Speak, Lord, for Thy servant heareth.” If I have not cultivated this devotion of hearing, I can only hear Gods voice at certain times; at other times I am taken up with things things which I say I must do, and I become deaf to Him, I am not living the life of a child. Have I heard Gods voice to-day?

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 02/14/2012

Whatever I tell you in the dark, speak in the light; and what you hear in the ear, preach on the housetops Matthew 10:27

Once we come to the conclusion that God still speaks to His children, we must then take on the discipline of hearing what He has to say, and then sharing with His other Children, as this is one way He has always used in communicating His will and His ways.

Chambers in todays devotion in his devotional classic My Utmost for His Highest begins with;

Sometimes God puts us through the experience and discipline of darkness to teach us to hear and obey Him.

From the worlds point of view, I guess the darkest hours of my life thus far was back in 1999 when my Lord first chose me to begin sharing with me visions and revelations of His will and His ways, and what was about to take place and what I was to share with the people. My health was in such shape that I actually purchased cemetery property, as they gave me less than six months to live, because of old, bad lifestyle choices.

In todays devotional time my Lord reminded me of some of these things and was told to share here with my reader. The primary thing which was brought to my attention was the great need within the church in America today was love relationships, people who truly loved and cared about one another, those who would take a genuine interest in those individuals who my Lord had been sending to these congregations. I was shown once again the great need of friends, and the Body of Christ working in unity to show a hurting world the love Christ our Lord has for it in very practical ways. It is very interesting today is Valentines Day. Some may simply shrug this off, but I choose to believe my God is speaking to me. I was lead to Ecclesiastes 4:9-12 and todays devotional in RBCs ministrys daily devotional Our Daily Bread.

Ecclesiastes 4:9-12

New International Version (NIV)

9 Two are better than one,
because they have a good return for their labor:
10 If either of them falls down,
one can help the other up.
But pity anyone who falls
and has no one to help them up.
11 Also, if two lie down together, they will keep warm.
But how can one keep warm alone?
12 Though one may be overpowered,
two can defend themselves.

A cord of three strands is not quickly broken

Wow! This is exactly what the United Missions of Maxima is all about. This is exactly one of the primary things my Lord first began showing me concerning ways in which His Church in America must come around. The whole vision of Maxima is all about uniting all the true followers of Christ our Lord into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body of Christ, to maximize our individual God given talents and resources to build up the Kingdom of God, to be there for one another to build one another up, as opposed to tearing one another down. We are called to a ministry of reconciliation. We are to be there to forgive one another as opposed to judging one anothers inadequacies.

Dennis Fisher, author of todays devotional in Our Daily Bread begins by telling us about Cicero.

Cicero was one of the greatest thinkers of the Roman Empire. He was a skilled orator, lawyer, politician, linguist, and writer. Still today he is quoted for his clear prose and practical wisdom.

For instance, of having friends he wrote: Friendship improves happiness and abates misery, by the doubling of our joy and the dividing of our grief. He understood the double benefits of friendship along lifes journey

Nearly a millennium earlier, King Solomon had written about the value of friends as well.

See Scripture above. Certainly a life without friends makes our sojourn lonely and hard to bear.

That famous Roman and that Jewish king were right: Friends are important. Friends serve as confidants, counselors, and burden-sharers. Think what it might mean for those who come visiting your local church in the future if you made it known to them that you want more than anything to be their friend as opposed to their adversary. Think what it might mean to them if as opposed to judging them if they may or may not fit into your little church click, that you instead just thought how much God cares for them, and how you might befriend them.

Imagine if you can what it might be like if all the churches across this land might take this same approach! I assure you of this one thing, those seeking truth will be more receptive in at least listening.

So, Go is still speaking to His loyal servants. Sometimes to get through to us though He has to take us through the dark night of the soul. Perhaps this is the key to Him speaking. Perhaps He only speaks directly to those so abandoned of themselves to His Lordship, to those loyal servants. Whatever the case, His major concern is a very real, very personal, very intimate, loving caring, eternal relationship with His children, and that we have this same intimate relationship with one another.

He has shown me very specifically, that by us displaying this love for our Lord and one another, a watching world might see this and then desire to have fellowship with His true followers, and then and only then may we take this once great nation back to God.

Intimate Moment With A Prophet 02/18/2012

Over the last several days, in my devotions and meditations, the Spirit has lead me concerning initiative, something I have been shown many of the churches across America today is lacking. First and foremost I am lead to the thought that; None of us liveth to himself.

Romans 14:1-8

New International Version (NIV)

Romans 14

The Weak and the Strong

1Accept the one whose faith is weak, without quarreling over disputable matters. 2 One persons faith allows them to eat anything, but another, whose faith is weak, eats only vegetables. 3 The one who eats everything must not treat with contempt the one who does not, and the one who does not eat everything must not judge the one who does, for God has accepted them. 4Who are you to judge someone elses servant? To their own master, servants stand or fall. And they will stand, for the Lord is able to make them stand.

5One person considers one day more sacred than another; another considers every day alike. Each of them should be fully convinced in their own mind. 6 Whoever regards one day as special does so to the Lord. Whoever eats meat does so to the Lord, for they give thanks to God; and whoever abstains does so to the Lord and gives thanks to God. 7 For none of us lives for ourselves alone, and none of us dies for ourselves alone. 8 If we live, we live for the Lord; and if we die, we die for the Lord. So, whether we live or die, we belong to the Lord.

In America, and for that matter, all over the world, there have been whole denominations formed only due to quarrels over such things as the day of the week we are to keep sacred. There are others who have been formed because some are in disagreement as to what signs of the Spirit must show in order to know one is truly saved, such as some say, if you have the indwelling of the Holy Spirit, you must show that you can speak in Spiritual tongues.

To my knowledge, I have never spoken in tongues in a Spiritual sense. I personally have a dear friend and brother, who is a pastor, as well a member of the United Missions of Maxima. He knows very well I am completely filled with the Holy Spirit of God, yet we have had this discussion many times, regarding tongues. He finally came to the conclusion, being that He knew I was filled with the Spirit; I had probably spoken in tongues and was not aware. Which this might be a good thing, being that I do not know for certain whether I have or havent, as I might have and was not made aware, but we have at least agreed to disagree on this one and not divide the Body of Christ over it.

My point is; God is extremely concerned in how denominations have divided the Body of Christ over things we do not need to be over zealous over. He is much more concerned that we be our brothers keeper. So I ask my reader; are you your brothers keeper? Chambers in his devotional for February 15 states concerning this;

Has it ever dawned on you that you are responsible for other souls spiritually before God?

instance, if I allow any private deflection from God in my life, everyone about me suffers. We “sit together in heavenly places.” “Whether one member suffer, all the members suffer with it.” When once you allow physical selfishness, mental slovenliness, moral obtuseness, spiritual density, everyone belonging to your crowd will suffer. “But,” you say, “who is sufficient for these things if you erect a standard like that?” “Our sufficiency is of God,” and of Him alone

“Ye shall be My witnesses.” How many of us are willing to spend every ounce of nervous energy, of mental, moral and spiritual energy we have for Jesus Christ? That is the meaning of a witness in Gods sense of the word

My life as a worker is the way I say “thank you” to God for His unspeakable salvation. Remember it is quite possible for any one of us to be flung out as reprobate silver “. . . lest that by any means when I have preached to others, I myself should be a castaway.”

Hmmm, something else for us to argue over, isnt it? I mean some say, it is impossible for one to fall from grace. I ask then who is able to commit the unpardonable sin other than one who has received the Spirit? What our precious Lord wants more than anything is that we are there for one another, to love the Lord our God with all our heart, soul and mind, and to love our neighbor as ourselves. He is concerned in us being an undivided body!

What our Lord is concerned with in this generation is that we arise from the dead, like in generations He has instructed before.

The Inspiration Of Spiritual Initiative

Arise from the dead. Ephesians5:14

Ephesians 5:1-14

New International Version (NIV)

Ephesians 5

1 Follow Gods example, therefore, as dearly loved children 2 and walk in the way of love, just as Christ loved us and gave himself up for us as a fragrant offering and sacrifice to God.

3 But among you there must not be even a hint of sexual immorality, or of any kind of impurity, or of greed, because these are improper for Gods holy people. 4 Nor should there be obscenity, foolish talk or coarse joking, which are out of place, but rather thanksgiving. 5 For of this you can be sure: No immoral, impure or greedy personsuch a person is an idolaterhas any inheritance in the kingdom of Christ and of God. 6 Let no one deceive you with empty words, for because of such things Gods wrath comes on those who are disobedient. 7 Therefore do not be partners with them.

8For you were once darkness, but now you are light in the Lord. Live as children of light 9 (for the fruit of the light consists in all goodness, righteousness and truth) 10 and find out what pleases the Lord. 11 Have nothing to do with the fruitless deeds of darkness, but rather expose them. 12 It is shameful even to mention what the disobedient do in secret. 13 But everything exposed by the light becomes visibleand everything that is illuminated becomes a light. 14 This is why it is said:

Wake up, sleeper,
rise from the dead,
and Christ will shine on you.

And the Spirit called out to me; Remember, I am yearning to find some within the church across America today who are willing to arise from the dead, and to become true disciples of Christ! This is why we called you!

Yes, yes, my Lord, yet I have tried, and find it extremely difficult. I cannot find even a few who are willing to speak to me concerning these things. It is as if they are blind. You know I have been visiting a particular church regularly since arriving here in Texas, Sunday mornings, evening, Wednesday evenings, as well as every study they may be engaged in, but nothing. I have left messages with associate pastors, spoke with another associate pastor, and even the senior pastor, telling them I have interest in making their church my church home, just wanted to speak with them to see whether my calling to ministry might be used within their body. I cannot even get them to return my call. What would those outside the Kingdom of God think about such a response?

The problem within the churches across America today is that they have been dead so long, they must take the initiative, however, it is not like taking an initiative from a worlds point of view, they must have us inspire the initiative, and for us to do so, they must have a real hunger and thirst for us to do so, yet like the children of old, they have become dissatisfied with the manna (The very WORD OF GOD) we supply them with.

Chambers states in his devotional My Utmost for His Highest for February 16;

All initiative is not inspired. A man may say to you “Buck up, take your disinclination by the throat, throw it overboard, and walk out into the thing!” That is ordinary human initiative. But when the Spirit of God comes in and says, in effect, “Buck up,” we find that the initiative is inspired

We all have any number of visions and ideals when we are young, but sooner or later we find that we have no power to make them real. We cannot do the things we long to do, and we are apt to settle down to the visions and ideals as dead, and God has to come and say “Arise from the dead.” When the inspiration of God does come, it comes with such miraculous power that we are able to arise from the dead and do the impossible thing. The remarkable thing about spiritual initiative is that the life comes after we do the “bucking up.” God does not give us overcoming life; He gives us life as we overcome

So, our dear servant, it is your job, the job we have called you to, to go and create in these people the desire, to at least let them know we are still attentive. We know very well, there are many within the churches who want to do that which is right, they have simply given over to death, so they must pray diligently that we might give them the Spiritual initiative.

We must arise from the dead, and we must have the power and presence of the Holy Spirit to give to us this Spiritual initiative. To have this power and presence we must abandon ourselves to the Lordship of Christ! The point is laid out in some of Chambers closing words in this devotion

When the inspiration of God comes, and He says “Arise from the dead,” we have to get up; God does not lift us up.

Are any of my readers ready to get up with me today? Is anyone ready to arise from the dead with me? I am lead today to understand all this to mean, for us to receive the power by the Spirit to arise from the dead, for us to receive the Spiritual initiative, we must first take the initiative to at least get up. Unfortunately, I am also lead to believe so many within the church have become exasperated and exhausted in trying to get up, when much of the churches leadership today is more concerned in their denominations agenda as opposed to our Lords. I am lead to believe many within the church are simply in despair. I have also been lead to believe there are also many who are seeking some kind of sign, for God to come down from Heaven and show many wonders, when most of the time our Lord speaks directly to us in the most simple ways.

Arise and eat1 Kings 19:5

1 Kings 19:3-9

New International Version (NIV)

3 Elijah was afraid and ran for his life. When he came to Beersheba in Judah, he left his servant there, 4 while he himself went a days journey into the wilderness. He came to a broom bush, sat down under it and prayed that he might die. I have had enough, LORD, he said. Take my life; I am no better than my ancestors. 5 Then he lay down under the bush and fell asleep.

All at once an angel touched him and said, Get up and eat.

He looked around, and there by his head was some bread baked over hot coals, and a jar of water. He ate and drank and then lay down again.

7 The angel of the LORD came back a second time and touched him and said, Get up and eat, for the journey is too much for you. 8 So he got up and ate and drank. Strengthened by that food, he traveled forty days and forty nights until he reached Horeb, the mountain of God. 9 There he went into a cave and spent the night.

The LORD Appears to Elijah

And the word of the LORD came to him: What are you doing here, Elijah?

I have found that so many times God speaks to us directly in such simple ways we do not even recognize it to be Him when He does speak. So many of us are awaiting Him to say something magnificent, that we miss Him all together when He does speak. This is a major reason we spend so much time at the United Missions of Maxima teaching in how God speaks to His children and how to recognize His voice when He does speak.

In Chambers devotional for February 17 He too takes notice of this;

The angel in this passage did not give Elijah a vision, or explain the Scriptures to him, or do anything remarkable. He simply told Elijah to do a very ordinary thing, that is, to get up and eat

What got us to this subject was depression, and how I felt lead to believe many within the church today have simply become depressed, and I would venture to say that in the passage above that Elijah had reached a very depressed part of his life journey. If we were never depressed, we would not be aliveonly material things dont suffer depression. If human beings were not capable of depression, we would have no capacity for happiness and exaltation. My study was leading us to take the initiative against depression.

Chambers continues his discourse;

When the Spirit of God comes to us, He does not give us glorious visions, but He tells us to do the most ordinary things imaginable. Depression tends to turn us away from the everyday things of Gods creation. But whenever God steps in, His inspiration is to do the most natural, simple things-things we would never have imagined God was in, but as we do them we find Him there. The inspiration that comes to us in this way is an initiative against depression. But we must take the first step and do it in the inspiration of God. If, however, we do something simply to overcome our depression, we will only deepen it. But when the Spirit of God leads us instinctively to do something, the moment we do it the depression is gone. As soon as we arise and obey, we enter a higher plane of life.

I cannot tell you the number of individuals I counsel because of depression, and as I have alluded to, so many even within the church of our day, and so many times the answers are so very simple if we will just allow our wonderful Lord to speak to us, and we were simply attuned to recognize His voice when He is speaking.

For an example, just through my writings here, God has spoken to many concerning the lack of love He has noticed even within His church, and how He has given us a ministry of reconciliation and love. One of the simple ways God chose to speak to His people is through

His people, thus He has spoken this message to you through me.

So, according to Chambers above; But when the Spirit of God leads us instinctively to do something, the moment we do it the depression is gone. As soon as we arise and obey, we enter a higher plane of life.

Pretty simple stuff, yes? Yet depression persists in our culture today, and at rates that are alarming! As true Disciples of Christ, we must take the initiative against depression. It is a sad day in Americas church history where someone from the outside who is suffering from depression comes in seeking to find the truths of Christ, only to leave more depressed than when they arrive, and believe you me, many will come tomorrow morning and experience just that. It is past time for us to arise from the dead and shine as Disciples of Christ! And, what is up with pastors today referring someone suffering from depression to a secular counselor to simply medicate the problem when Christ our Lord whom they profess has the answers.

So, I have spoken much today about taking initiative in certain areas, and I could go on and on, but will stop with one last initiative, that is the Initiative against despair, being that is tied into the others.

Taking the Initiative Against Despair

Rise, let us be going Matthew 26:46

Matthew 26:39-46

New International Version (NIV)

39 Going a little farther, he fell with his face to the ground and prayed, My Father, if it is possible, may this cup be taken from me. Yet not as I will, but as you will.

40 Then he returned to his disciples and found them sleeping. Couldnt you men keep watch with me for one hour? he asked Peter. 41 Watch and pray so that you will not fall into temptation. The spirit is willing, but the flesh is weak.

42 He went away a second time and prayed, My Father, if it is not possible for this cup to be taken away unless I drink it, may your will be done.

43 When he came back, he again found them sleeping, because their eyes were heavy. 44 So he left them and went away once more and prayed the third time, saying the same thing.

45 Then he returned to the disciples and said to them, Are you still sleeping and resting? Look, the hour has come, and the Son of Man is delivered into the hands of sinners. 46 Rise! Let us go! Here comes my betrayer!

Now, I am certain all the church goers in todays culture would have remained wide awake with our Lord, especially considering this grief stricken hour our Lord was facing.

Chambers states in his devotional for February 18;

In the Garden of Gethsemane, the disciples went to sleep when they should have stayed awake, and once they realized what they had done it produced despair. The sense of having done something irreversible tends to make us despair. We say, Well, its all over and ruined now; whats the point in trying anymore. If we think this kind of despair is an exception, we are mistaken.

It is a very ordinary human experience. Whenever we realize we have not taken advantage of a magnificent opportunity, we are apt to sink into despair.

Is this where the church in America is today? I know for a fact, there are so many who want to do the right thing, who wants to be true Disciples of Christ. Have we all just succumbed to despair by listening to Satans lies and deceits? Chambers continues his discourse;

But Jesus comes and lovingly says to us, in essence, Sleep on now. That opportunity is lost forever and you cant change that. But get up, and lets go on to the next thing. In other words, let the past sleep, but let it sleep in the sweet embrace of Christ, and let us go on into the invincible future with Him.

I am convinced that the church in America got off track after all our great theologians began stuying the liberal theology of the Germans just after WW II. This is when we began to teach Christianity intellectually verses relationally. My dear brothers and sisters, about anything I have come to know about Christ my Lord and His marvelous Kingdom, cant be explained intellectually, but is all about relationship, relationship, relationship. First and foremost, it is about a very real, very intimate, loving, caring, eternal relationship with our Lord Jesus Christ, and the second is like that, the same intimate relationship with all our brothers and sisters of the Kingdom of God.

I am convinced we have made serious mistakes along this line. However, we must ask ourselves; do we continue sleeping, or arise from the dead. Are we prepared to let the past sleep in the sweet embrace of Christ and go on into the invincible future with our Lord? Are we now ready to be true Disciples of Christ?
