Intimate Moment With A Prophet 03/03/2012

Prophet on the Bay

Dr. Kristian Shepard

I have spent the last several weeks discussing with my reader something I felt compelled by the Spirit to share, as I felt so many in America today no longer truly believe God still actually speaks. So, I have spent several days on just that, God still speaks in very audible ways to His children. I have also spent considerable time trying to show that our Lords major concern with His creation, and more important the Pinnacle of His creation, man, is a very real, very intimate love relationship with us, and that we know we have such relationship with our creator by having this same intimate relationship with all who are of the Kingdom of God.

I hope I have been able to convey to anyone who had thought or wondered if God still speaks that He does. I also hope and pray that I have conveyed how much our Lord wants to have a very real very intimate relationship with His people, and that He truly would love for everyone to come to Him and enjoy this wonderful relationship, a relationship which surpasses any other by leaps and bounds. It is my prayer also that I have conveyed that we must be there for one another in this Kingdom relationship.

Today I hope to touch on a few topics which will wrap up this idea. Here I would like to begin with what I hope one will see the value of the United Missions of Maxima, and the reason it was formed to begin with, as well as why I have said repeatedly that this is God ordained and something we must do. I am lead first to a couple of Scriptures. First, John 14: 25-31;

John 14:25-31

New International Version (NIV)

25 All this I have spoken while still with you. 26But the Advocate, the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my name, will teach you all things and will remind you of everything I have said to you. 27 Peace I leave with you; my peace I give you. I do not give to you as the world gives. Do not let your hearts be troubled and do not be afraid.

28 You heard me say, I am going away and I am coming back to you. If you loved me, you would be glad that I am going to the Father, for the Father is greater than I. 29 I have told you now before it happens, so that when it does happen you will believe. 30 I will not say much more to you, for the prince of this world is coming. He has no hold over me, 31 but he comes so that the world may learn that I love the Father and do exactly what my Father has commanded me.

The first thing I would like to point out is the very first part of this scripture concerning the Holy Spirit. Christ had to live, die, and be resurrected and return to the Father in order to send Advocate. He sent His very own Spirit to live within us. Once we totally abandon ourself to the Lordship of Christ He promises He will totally fill us with His Holy Spirit.

The problem I have been shown with so very many within the church across America today is the amount of room, or the amount of ourselves we are willing to give the Lordship of Christ, thus giving that room within us for this Spirit to reside. So many have simply given the Spirit just a mother-in-law suite at best. Then we wonder why we do not see things happening within our church walls as they did in Acts. We wonder why we can no longer move mountains. The reason is really very simple. We have not totally abandoned ourselves to the

Lordship of Christ, thus His Spirit is so very limited in the space within us to show His power.

However, when filled with the Very Spirit of Christ our Lord, there is no more a intimate relationship, the relationship our Lord so wants with His children. This is a relationship I feel most within the church truly seeks with the Lord. Unfortunately, they simply do not have the faith to let go of the world and abandon themselves to the Lordship of Christ.

Drudgery is one of the finest tests to determine the genuineness of our character. Drudgery is work that is far removed from anything we think of as ideal work. It is the utterly hard, menial, tiresome, and dirty work. (Chambers)

Oswald Chambers gives us some clues in his daily devotional My Utmost for His Highest on February 19.

Arise, shine . . . Isaiah 60:1

Chambers in this particular devotional gives us an idea of where the church may be leaning off the right road. He begins his discourse with;

When it comes to taking the initiative against drudgery, we have to take the first step as though there were no God. There is no point in waiting for God to help us He will not. But once we arise, immediately we find He is there. Whenever God gives us His inspiration, suddenly taking the initiative becomes a moral issue a matter of obedience.

I have been shown over and over by the leading of the Spirit, emphatically, that if the church goers in the United States would simply get up and begin doing what it already know very well it is supposed to be doing, we could totally revolutionize the church in America today and take America back to God. If we will arise and shine, drudgery will be divinely transformed.

Drudgery is one of the finest tests to determine the genuineness of our character. Drudgery is work that is far removed from anything we think of as ideal work. It is the utterly hard, menial, tiresome, and dirty work. And when we experience it, our spirituality is instantly tested and we will know whether or not we are spiritually genuine. Read John 13. In this chapter, we see the Incarnate God performing the greatest example of drudgery washing fishermens feet. He then says to them, If I then, your Lord and Teacher, have washed your feet, you also ought to wash one anothers feet (John 13:14).(Chambers Feb 19)

Do you suppose your reader understands that it is Us speaking to hem now through yourself and Chambers?

I pray that they do. However, it seems everyone has lost their faith as far as you still speaking.

Have they forgotten what is recorded in Acts 2:17;

Acts 2:17

New International Version (NIV)

17 In the last days, God says,
I will pour out my Spirit on all people.
Your sons and daughters will prophesy,
your young men will see visions,
your old men will dream dreams.

It appears so my Lord. You know the number of pastors and church leaders I have carried the message you sent me with to them. You know how they all dismissed it as rubbish. May God have mercy on their soul!

As I have told you, prophets are like trees, they are both planted for the future. Think how history would have been so much different if the people had paid any attention to the prophets of old. It is your job to simply speak what I give you to speak.

Yes Lord, please continue to speak. I will simply do as I am told

In Chambers devotional for February 20 he continues his discourse concerning the Initiative against dreaming. Here he focuses on dreaming when we should be doing.

Daydreaming about something in order to do it properly is right, but daydreaming about it when we should be doing it is wrong when our inclination is to spend time daydreaming over what we have already been told to do, it is unacceptable and Gods blessing is never on it. God will take the initiative against this kind of daydreaming by prodding us to action. His instructions to us will be along the lines of this: Dont sit or stand there, just go!

This is exactly what I was saying about the church in America today. If only they would go and do what they already know to do we could totally revolutionize the church and take America back to God. However, we continue with another Bible Study course, and this has become their act of worship.

However, this leads me back to relationship, relationship, relationship, that our Lords major concern is relationship with His Children. Before my reader thinks for a moment I am referring in the above paragraph just about service, they are wrong. In fact, it seems to me that this intimate relationship with our Lord and one another is even more important than service.

Chambers in the very next days devotion February 21 ask Have you ever been carried away for Him?

DO YOU REALLY LOVE HIM?

Scripture Mark 14:3-9

Mark 14:3-9

New International Version (NIV)

3 While he was in Bethany, reclining at the table in the home of Simon the Leper, a woman came with an alabaster jar of very expensive perfume, made of pure nard. She broke the jar and poured the perfume on his head.

4 Some of those present were saying indignantly to one another, Why this waste of perfume? 5 It could have been sold for more than a years wages[a] and the money given to the poor. And they rebuked her harshly.

6 Leave her alone, said Jesus. Why are you bothering her? She has done a beautiful thing to me. 7 The poor you will always have with you,[b] and you can help them any time you want. But you will not always have me. 8 She did what she could. She poured perfume on my body beforehand to prepare for my burial. 9 Truly I tell you, wherever the gospel is preached throughout the world, what she has done will also be told, in memory of her.

This scripture should be a pretty good indication of how important a intimate relationship with His people are to Him. Chambers begins his discussion in this devotional with;

If what we call love doesnt take us beyond ourselves, it is not really love. If we have the idea that love is characterized as cautious, wise, sensible, shrewd, and never taken to extremes, we have missed the true meaning. This may describe affection and it may bring us a warm feeling, but it is not a true and accurate description of love.

I ask you my reader, take a look around in your own local church, is this the kind of love most have for our wonderful Lord or is more like the description of affection? Chambers continues his discourse;

Have you ever been driven to do something for God not because you felt that it was useful or your duty to do so, or that there was anything in it for you, but simply because you love Him? Have you ever realized that you can give things to God that are of value to Him? Or are you just sitting around daydreaming about the greatness of His redemption, while neglecting all the things you could be doing for Him?

There are times when it seems as if God watches to see if we will give Him even small gifts of surrender, just to show how genuine our love is for Him. To be surrendered to God is of more value than our personal holiness. Concern over our personal holiness causes us to focus our eyes on ourselves, and we become overly concerned about the way we walk and talk and look, out of fear of offending God. . . . but perfect love casts out fear . . . once we are surrendered to God (1 John 4:18). We should quit asking ourselves, Am I of any use? and accept the truth that we really are not of much use to Him. The issue is never of being of use, but of being of value to God Himself. Once we are totally surrendered to God, He will work through us all the time.

See how many times Chambers refers to surrender? This is what I am speaking when I say total abandonment. When once we realize by total abandonment of ourselves to the Lordship of Christ not only shows our Lord the love we have for Him, thus strengthening that relationship, but by so doing we are also becoming of more value to Him and the work He can do through us. It is here we learn we can truly live a life free of fear and worry, full of nothing but joy and happiness all the time.

If only the churched can come to terms with the fact, that serving others is serving the Lord, and this is where we find the greatest contentment, the greatest peace, the most wonderful experience life has to offer, that we will also find, it is through this total abandonment of self that we find the power of the Holy Spirit of God that we are indeed able to move mountains.

Believe me, I was shown how this is what our Lord wants! I have been shown how a outside world is watching the churched very carefully, and wanting to see this love we talk and preach about being manifested through those of us who talk about it. They are watching to see this power of the Spirit manifested through us, not just simply hear us talk about it, and this must be done through a unified voice. Then, and only then, will the watching world come into the Kingdom by the droves, like in waves on the sea shore, and it is then we may take this once great nation back to God. But, we who profess Christ must have real faith. It is time we shared with a watching world that we truly believe what we say we believe.

Chambers tells us in another devotional this past month, February 22. He calls this the discipline of Spiritual Tenacity. He calls tenacity here perseverance.We must first be like the Psalmist and be still and know that He is truly God, that He is Lord of Lords.

“Perseverance is more than endurance. It is endurance combined with absolute assurance and certainty that what we are looking for is going to happen. Perseverance means more than just hanging on, which may be only exposing our fear of letting go and falling.

This is where most within the church in America today are, simply hanging on, simply the fear of letting go.

Yes Lord, as you have shown me over and over, just there in case there is really anything to all this Christian thing, not going to venture out too deep into it, but getting a little wet, just in case there is something, they would hate to see the expression on their friends faces then. However, it appears to me that many within the church are simply afraid in God not succeeding more than anything else. As Chambers continues his discussion of this, I believe he concludes this as well.

Perseverance is our supreme effort of refusing to believe that our hero is going to be conquered. Our greatest fear is not that we will be damned, but that somehow Jesus Christ will be defeated. Also, our fear is that the very things our Lord stood for love, justice, forgiveness, and kindness among men will not win out in the end and will represent an unattainable goal for us. Then there is the call to spiritual perseverance. A call not to hang on and do nothing, but to work deliberately, knowing with certainty that God will never be defeated.

This is where the people must get to in order to ever take America back to God!

If our hopes seem to be experiencing disappointment right now, it simply means that they are being purified. Every hope or dream of the human mind will be fulfilled if it is noble and of God. But one of the greatest stresses in life is the stress of waiting for God. He brings fulfillment, because you have kept My command to persevere . . . (Revelation 3:10).

We must continue to persevere spiritually. But we must also have the determination to serve! Chambers continues into the next days devotional;

The Determination to Serve

The Son of Man did not come to be served, but to serve . . .Matthew 20:28

Pauls idea of service was the same as our Lords . . . ourselves your bondservants for Jesus sake (2 Corinthians 4:5). We somehow have the idea that a person called to the ministry is called to be different and above other people. But according to Jesus Christ, he is called to be a doormat for others called to be their spiritual leader, but never their superior

Yes, you have all been called to ministry!

Pauls idea of service was to pour his life out to the last drop for others. And whether he received praise or blame made no difference. As long as there was one human being who did not know Jesus, Paul felt a debt of service to that person until he did come to know Him. But the chief motivation behind Pauls service was not love for others but love for his Lord. If our devotion is to the cause of humanity, we will be quickly defeated and broken-hearted, since we will often be confronted with a great deal of ingratitude from other people

What is so lacking in the church in America today is this kind of love, first from the pastors, and then the church leadership. For if this kind of love is not prevalent from the church leadership it will never be within the flock. And, if the flock cannot show that the Love of

Christ manifested within themselves, the watching world only witnesses them talk, and thus, since they do not actually manifest this love, the watching world simply assumes they do not even believe what they say they believe, for it is certainly not obvious. Consequently, we simply have people in the churches across America moving from church to church seeking to find a church home that gives to them what they feel they need, and very few un-churched finding Christ.

I feel Chambers in his devotional classic My Utmost for His Highest for day February 25th sums it all up most appropriately. He begins with the Scripture 2 Corinthians 12:15.This devotional speaks volumes of what is needed most within the church in America today, for until we can have this, we will never take America back to God.

The Destitution of Service

2 Corinthians 12:11-18

New International Version (NIV)

Pauls Concern for the Corinthians

11I have made a fool of myself, but you drove me to it. I ought to have been commended by you, for I am not in the least inferior to the super-apostles, even though I am nothing. 12 I persevered in demonstrating among you the marks of a true apostle, including signs, wonders and miracles. 13 How were you inferior to the other churches, except that I was never a burden to you? Forgive me this wrong!

14 Now I am ready to visit you for the third time, and I will not be a burden to you, because what I want is not your possessions but you. After all, children should not have to save up for their parents, but parents for their children. 15 So I will very gladly spend for you everything I have and expend myself as well. If I love you more, will you love me less? 16 Be that as it may, I have not been a burden to you. Yet, crafty fellow that I am, I caught you by trickery! 17 Did I exploit you through any of the men I sent to you? 18 I urged Titus to go to you and I sent our brother with him. Titus did not exploit you, did he? Did we not walk in the same footsteps by the same Spirit?

From this scripture the very first thing which catches my attention is verses 11-12. Since my call to ministry, this is exactly how I have felt. I have carried the message which was given me by our wonderful Lord, that I was instructed by Him to take to the churches, only to be shunned by the church leadership. At first I had thought it was because of my in-experience. So I returned to school to get my ph. D. in pastorate ministry, but still I have been shunned.

Perhaps the church leadership should have taken notice because I persevered in demonstrating among you the marks of a true apostle, including signs, wonders and miracles. I cannot tell you the number of individuals I have seen healed by God through my obedience. Yet, still I am shunned.

Iwas finally told by my Lord, it is not me that they fear, but God, for they are more concerned with their own denominations agenda than they are with Gods.

All I can say to this is; wake up church leadership in America! It is not your church denomination who can save you, only our precious Lord Jesus Christ! And, you will be judged according to what you have said and done.

As I said earlier, I think Chambers in February 25th devotional sums up the need in our churches today better than I can. He begins with;

Natural human love expects something in return. But Paul is saying, It doesnt really matter to me whether you love me or not. I am willing to be completely destitute anyway; willing to be poverty-stricken, not just for your sakes, but also that I may be able to get you to God.

This and only this should be the concern of each and every church leader in America today, that they may be able to get the people to God. It was a joyful thing to Paul.

The institutional churchs idea of a servant of God is not at all like Jesus Christs idea. His idea is that we serve Him by being the servants of others. Jesus Christ actually out-socialized the socialists. He said that in His kingdom the greatest one would be the servant of all (seeMatthew 23:11). The real test of a saint is not ones willingness to preach the gospel, but ones willingness to do something like washing the disciples feet that is, being willing to do those things that seem unimportant in human estimation but count as everything to God.

Is this the general consensus in your church? Chambers continues;

But before we will serve, we stop to ponder our personal and financial concerns What if God wants me to go over there? And what about my salary? What is the climate like there? Who will take care of me? Paul focused his life on Jesus Christs idea of a New Testament saint; that is, not one who merely proclaims the gospel, but one who becomes broken bread and poured-out wine in the hands of Jesus Christ for the sake of others.

Is this what your church leadership is?

I will close for now and wrap up this introductory series for this new year. In going into the new year my prayer was to share time with my reader to accomplish a few things. I pray I have done just what I set out to do.

First, through spending time with me in my intimate prayer, study, and meditation time, I pray that you have witnessed beyond a shadow of a doubt that God is very much alive and well today and still speaks very clearly and audible to His children. It is also my prayer that you have come to realize that more than anything else our wonderful Lord wants a very real, very intimate relationship with you, and that we are to have this same intimate relationship with all our brothers and sisters in the Kingdom of God, and not only that, but we are to truly love our Neighbor as ourselves. Rebember; I am willing to be completely destitute anyway; willing to be poverty-stricken, not just for your sakes, but also that I may be able to get you to God.

Finally, my dear brothers and sisters, it is my prayer that I have conveyed to you the urgency there is to take America back to God before He completely condemns us, and to do this we must first take the church in America back to God.

In order to do this, we must first realize God is all about relationship, first and foremost a very real very intimate relationship with His Children, and then we are to have this same love for one another, to be there for one another. We are but ONE BODY OF CHRIST, there is but one Lord Jesus, One God, and One Holy Spirit. We are to unite in this one BODY OF CHRIST in the ministry of reconciliation, for we must first realize how God reconciled us to Himself, so we are to be willing to reconcile everyone to us. We have to be more about love and less about judging others.

Witness how you may join this unity of the Body of Christ at www.umomaxima.org and see how we share the love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways at www.hoperetreatsinternational.org. TAKING AMERICA BACK TO GOD

BY AN INTIMATE MOMENT WITH A PROPHET

Over the last couple months the Spirit has certainly been speaking along certain lines, and I presume my reader has picked up on this if they have followed me in Intimate Moment With A Prophet.I pray you have read each of these Intimate Moments in order they were written, for this is the order by which the Spirit spoke it to me. One of the most prevalent points the Spirit has spoken is that God is in the process of judging America, and if we are to have any chance in taking this once great nation back to God, we must first take the church in America back to God.

If you have not already done so, I ask that you now please go back and read these intimate moments with the Spirit of God, but before you do so, go first to God in prayer asking that He lead you to what exactly He wants you to get from these writings.

I started out the first of the year with the Spirit speaking specific things to me and these specific things I wanted to convey to my reader. There were several other major points in addition to the urgency of taking America back to God. Another major point I felt compelled to stress was that the most important thing to God is a very real, a very intimate, personal, eternal relationship with His children, and that He is still speaking to His Children in very real ways. His Word is not the absolute only way by which God communicates with His children today. We are to also have this same intimate relationship with all who are of the Kingdom of God. A third point He was sharing with me and He wanted me to share with my reader was the importance of real discipleship within the church in America today in order to take the church back to God, thus giving us the power to take this once great nation back to God.

You see, in order to have the total filling of the Holy Spirit of God, thus having the power and presence of the Spirit, we must first totally abandon ourselves to the Lordship of Christ! If we only give a portion of ourselves, then the Spirit has only this small portion to come into us.

It is my earnest prayer that by sharing with me in these most intimate moments I have been able to convey to you these things I just mentioned. I must warn you though, even if you have gone to our Lord in prayer as I asked you to do, asking that He lead you through these intimate moments and to guide you to exactly what He wants you to receive from these writings, and He totally convicts your heart of these things, satan will surly rush in and try to take these things from you. For most of my readers, even their church community will try to take this away from you.

I feel compelled here to share a story with you, as I am sure you will see much more clearly what I am trying to say here from this little story. Because of the society we live in today, technology makes it easy to reach many people rather easy. So, on my facebook I have been trying to reach many with this message. One must first know, because I am in ministry, even finally finishing up my grad school from a Christian University, a very large amount of my friends on facebook are professed Christian.

I could not understand why it was so difficult to reach these people with this message of unity, when the Scripture is clear on One God, One Spirit, One Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ and One Body of Christ. I could not even get enough interest in unifying the Christian community in an all out effort to take America back to God to get anyone to respond. I finally came to the point of writing a simple question. The question is quoted here;

Simple Question/ Something of great concern to me!!! This brings me to ask a very important question here. Before I ask though, I must let the reader know, because I am in ministry, probably better than 90% of my FB friends are professed Christian.

NOW THE QUESTION;

It is quite obvious from my reading the many post here day after day that most of the Christian community is quite concerned with the moral fiber within our culture today, the direction our nation is heading, and the general attitude the media and our Government has towards the Christian community, I am specifically referring to a post yesterday, where there is a law in California that makes it illegal for Christians to gather in a private resident, so my question is; why is there so little interest in becoming involved with an organization that is all about uniting the Christian voice into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be, the one Body of Christ our Lord spoke about? I mean, if you are a part of a particular denomination who has a organized plan of uniting the Body of Christ and taking America back to God, I would love to hear about it. Seems to me most denominations are more concerned with their denominations agenda than they are in Gods. Otherwise, the Christian community could give me a reason for no interest in a united voice of true followers of Christ and truly becoming active in taking this once great nation back to God! Can we not at least open up a dialog in ways we might unite our voice and organize this voice to take America back to God or is it simply too late?

Response to Question

I didnt want to put a name with this response just in case my friend did not want to be quoted. However, this quote comes from a real friend who I know personally had spent considerable time in professional ministry in an organized main line denomination. I feel it is important to understand this from this perspective. I also want my reader to know I just had two others who even responded to this question with I like it. This response was the only one which actually gave my question any thought.

The problem you speak so truthfully about stems more from “organized religion” than from the lay brethren it serves. As a former salaried minister of an organized religious body, I speak from personal experience. O. R. is a political body, …or bodies, and it survives the same way any other corporation survives: dollars and cents. Each body must promote it’s own brand of Christianity as different and better than the competition in order to capture the necessary dollars to pay bloated executive salaries, excessively ornate worship centers, and expensive media advertising. American religion is big business, and very profitable these days. When I realized this, and how I had become a part of it, I resigned my office, and my allegiance to O. R. I reclaimed my “Abraham,” a person who worships God in his heart and mind, not in a building with a laundry list of religious “do’s and don’ts.” If you don’t approve of a product, stop buying it. If enough people stop buying the same product, it will go away.

How do we reclaim the sandal walking words of Jesus? Find your own Abraham. Go back to the spiritual village where we live a sermon daily, instead of listen passively to one on the weekend. Stand in the gap for the weak, encourage the children, fix the widow’s broken fence, drop off some food to the underemployed. And, like Abraham, we will be loved by God.

The first thing I would like to bring to the attention of my reader is again, this guy comes from Professional ministry, and that he became so disgusted with how the church has become more like the world as opposed to the church transforming the world, as it is commissioned to do, that he finally quit ministry. This is so very unfortunate! The second thing I certainly wanted to point out was just how big a business he had seen the church become, which is a great clue as to why it is near impossible to convince the churched of their need of unity in the body, and together share with a watching world the love that Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways. Which this leads me to the third very important point I believe this responder made; Stand in the gap for the weak, encourage the children, fix the widow’s broken fence, drop off some food to the underemployed.

This is exactly what the United Missions of Maxima is all about!!! This is the reason for us forming Hope Retreats International, that through a united effort we may show a watching world the real love that Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways, that we might together stand in the gap for the weak, encourage the children, fix the widows broken fence, and drop off some food to the underemployed. Finally, I would hope that my responder understands, that Maxima is truly a ministry without walls, other than the walls at any of our retreats where we are actually practicing ministry, sharing the love of Christ in practical ways, such as a Christ centered resident recovery program for battered abused women.

Unfortunately, because the church in America today has chosen to become more like any other business, most churches have to use somewhere in the neighborhood of 90% of their monthly budget to pay administration cost and their mortgage payment, leaving very little for actual ministry out into the community.

So, I have first been lead by the Holy Spirit of God to first understand that in order for us to have any chance of taking America back to God, we must first take the church in America back to God. It is past time that those on the outside cannot see any difference in the church than they can anywhere else in America. In fact, many had rather go anywhere else to avoid being judged by the church, condemned by the churched and then crucified by this same church just after fellowship dinner.

We must mentor the Christian into discipleship, as I am convinced one can be truly saved and not be a disciple, as salvation is all about grace from God, nothing more. However, I am certain we have fallen short in mentoring new Christians into the real lifestyle of a true follower of Christ. I am not here going to try to analyze whether or not someone deciding not to even become a disciple they will remain saved or not, as this will no doubt be judged by God, for there are many who are within the church walls today who have professed Christ as Lord, but plainly do not have any intention of becoming a disciple.

On the other hand, however, there are many who are truly moved by the Holy Spirit of God, and truly called to discipleship at conversion, who simply did not have anyone to turn to truly be mentored in the true Christian Lifestyle. You see, at Maxima we first of all believe without a question that each and every one of us was created by God for a specific purpose within the Kingdom of God. Our first job is to help an individual find exactly what that purpose is, for we have found that when one finds this specific purpose and determines to live it, this is where we find a life free of fear and worry, full of nothing but joy and happiness all the time. It is through true discipleship that one truly finds a world of contentment and peace, for this is exactly what an individual was created for to begin with.

Unfortunately, many spend an entire lifetime searching out this one thing. If they do not find truth, they will replace truth with a lie, some substitute it with drugs, some sex, and there are literally hundreds of things we can substitute this truth with.

We must then unite all these true followers of Christ into the one mind and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body of Christ. There have been whole denominations created over simple difference of interpretations of Scriptures. However, I know all Christian denominations believe and can agree on at least the first two that our Lord gave to us, which are to love the Lord our God with all our heart, with all our soul and with all our mind. And, the second is like it, to love our neighbor as ourselves. Finally I am certain all Christian denominations can agree on the last command our Lord gave to us prior to going back to be with the Father, which was to make disciples of all the nations. At Maxima, we just feel strongly that before we go out trying to make disciples of all the nations, we might should first make disciples of all the church goers. So, I ask my reader, can we unite under these three commands?

If we can, then as a united voice we can go out together sharing the love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways. Imagine what we can do together! As one united voice, think also how we might help shape our culture positively, how as one voice we may let our governments know what is expected of our elected officials, and as one voice just simply keep voting the official out until they get it right. One nation of true Christians, under God, indivisible, can indeed take this once great nation back to God! Divided, we are about to fall! I beg of you my dear brothers and sisters of the Kingdom of God, wake up!

It is not just me whom our Lord is speaking this too. There are many! We simply have to join forces! We have to get on the same side. We must stop judging our brothers and sisters over little things. I mean one church body sees drinking alcohol horrible, an unforgivable sin, others see smoking this way. I do not know if you realize it or not, but we have all sinned and fallen short of the glory of God, and will continue to do so. Have we forgotten where our Lord found us? Yet, our wonderful Lord reconciled us to Himself through His blood, and we have been given the ministry of reconciliation. Should we not start acting like it? We must stop condemning those who have come to us seeking truth.

Just yesterday I was at a church service and from the pulpit the pastor made this little gay joke, not really a joke, but if I were gay, I would have certainly felt bad about it. Is this right? Can Good not heal these people the way He healed us? Does He not love them? Should we not love them because they are sinning different than we are?

This same pastor also made a comment that the only way of communication that God has today for speaking to His Children was through His Word, the Bible. Well, I have to ask then, was I hallucinating then when my Lord took me by the hand and took me to destinations I didnt even know to share visions and revelations? It seems to me God is God, and He can certainly choose to speak in any way He wants, I mean He has even chosen to speak through the mouth of a jackass. This particular pastor was speaking strictly that God no longer gives revelations and visions any longer. Has God become different? I always thought He was unchanging? Interesting though, this same pastor just a few sentences later shared how the Lord had shared with him to come to this particular church. Seems to me this pastor was very opinionated, and things like this must stop.

This same pastor also got excited that his congregation gave a love offering of a couple thousand dollars to a foreign missionary his denomination supports. Now, I want my reader to completely understand that I have nothing what so ever against the support of foreign missionaries. However, this same church which gave like this is the same church that cannot seem to return my phones calls concerning how God may use me in their church and joining our local mission to take care of troubled teens. I am after all seeking a church home in this new community I am residing, as all Maxima brothers and sisters are encouraged to do.

We have to stop placing our wonderful GOD who created the heavens and the earth in such small boxes. We must unite! As I have stated, I am not the only one receiving these visions and revelations. For an example, James Robison seems to be getting some such messages. Have you read his new book, -INDIVISIBLE: Hope for the Future? In his own words;

For too long those who profess to have faith in the living God and claim to believe marriage, family, and freedom are important have hidden the light of truth under the covering of personal comfort, compromise, and unfruitful conformity. Now is the time to raise high the standard of liberating truth while standing together as one with the Father and other believers who love God in order to truly become the shining city on the hill that cannot and must not be hidden. INDIVISIBLE is our attempt to inspire all people of faith to find common ground for our common concerns. Together we can help correct our nations perilous course. (Found at http://jamesrobison.net/?q=node/122)

There are of course many others other than Mr. Robison, just serf the internet to find them. However, Mr. Robison is certainly a leader within the Christian community, one who is much more qualified than myself to lead just an organization as Maxima. I even wrote to him and offered to give him the reigns. Do you think he has responded? I did this mainly to show my reader that this has absolutely nothing to do with myself trying to set up an organization I can run and make a name for myself, and because I have just finished up my pd. D. and Mr. Robison already has many years in ministry, and already has a very large center of influence I determined he could at least get a strong foundation of a united voice to build upon.

As since my beginning in ministry, and beginning to organize this unified voice of true followers of Christ, I have been unable to put together a strong foundation. We have put together from time to time a group in numbers between a hundred or two, to only dwindle down again to nothing. It seems people get around us and are filled with the Holy Spirit, and then seem to get back into the world, get involved in their local church, only to become once again discouraged.

I just wish and I pray daily I can come up with just the right words to convince the people of this urgent need to unite into the One Body of Christ we were meant to be, so that we can go out into the world and show a watching world the love that Christ our Lord has for it in very practical ways. I pray I can convince the Christian community of the need to become an active voice in our local, state and then federal government to ever take this once great nation back to God. And, though, I have been shown this is the only way, and that in the event we do not, America is not going to survive as we know it. Even though I am a professional script writer for film and television I do not seem to be able to come up with adequate wordins to do the convincing. So, I simply continue to pray, and to share these visions and revelations God has given me to share.

I literally beat myself up over this! I mean I am in continuous battle with satan over these things. Such things as, why do many not even believe3, or do not seem to believe that God is, or can, or is still speaking to individuals today. Body Armor for the Culture War

http://jamesrobison.net/?q=node/120

Weve heard for years that were in the middle of a culture war. A culture war, unlike a civil war, is not fought with guns and tanks, but with ideas, words, arguments, media, and education. Unlike ordinary political debates, its a fight over the fundamental principles on which cultures are based.

The first two issuesabortion and religious freedomcome together with the recent U.S. Department of Health and Human Services mandate that organizations, including religious organizations, provide health insurance that covers sterilization, contraception and drugs that induce abortion.

The media has tried to turn this into a debate over contraception, which they portrayincorrectlyas a Catholic issue. In reality, all people of faith, indeed, all Americans have something to lose here. If the federal government can force its citizens to pay for things they find morally abhorrent, then there is nothing the government cant do.

An Email to James Robison from Dr. Randall Maxwell

February 29, 2012

James Robison;

I am Pastor Dr. Randall Maxwell, now living in Weatherford Texas, by divine appointment. I have just completed a research on your new book, which intrigued me, thus I researched as much as I could find on you. From everything I have found on you and what you believe and teach, I have been lead by the Holy Spirit to reach you with this email.

I must tell you to begin this discourse, I had spent my whole adult life in the film industry until 1999 when I finally totally abandoned myself to a ministry God had called me. I had actually argued with God for five years that He had chosen the wrong guy, before old lifestyle choices made my health in such bad condition I was forced to listen to God. My health had actually gotten so bad, I was given six months to live, and thus I had purchased cemetery property. I found it very easy to totally abandon myself to my Lord with just six months to live.

At any rate, this is where things in my life became very interesting. My Lord began showing me revelations and visions, taking me to places which seemed completely foreign, like from another galaxy. Once, lead by the Spirit I was taken to what I had thought was some level of heaven. However, I was told later by the Spirit that what I had witnessed was actually the United States after it had been judged and condemned by God and totally re-vegetated. While on this subject, I feel I must inject here, I am not some dooms day prophet trying to predict the end of the world. I am simply passing on to you what I have witnessed. However, if indeed we do not take America back to God, and He does indeed Judge and condemn America, with how closely knit the world financial system is, I cannot see the world surviving America going under.

At this time I do not want to bore you with the details. In fact, I pray that you do not get bored with this email, and that the Holy Spirit of God may keep your attention until the very end, as I am certain it is extremely important that you receive its message. It is my hope and prayer to at least keep your attention long enough to direct you to my websites where you can pray over the sites, and prayerfully the Spirit will lead you through them so that you may receive the message our God would have you receive from the sites. I go ahead and give you the sites here, just in case.

www.umomaxima.org & www.hoperetreatsinternational.org & www.maximavisionsproductions.com.

I ask that you first go to the umomaxima site and then go to the Vision page, as this page shares much of the vision that was first introduced to me on that unforgettable weekend I alluded to in the preceding paragraph.

It was during that weekend that my Lord first began sharing with me His displeasure with the USA and that He was about to begin judgment on her, and that I was called to lead America back to God. Remember, this was pre-911. Remember also, I had no experience in ministry what so ever, other than five years before I actually abandoned His call I had half hearted accepted and began study in ministry and began work at the LA mission, but held on to my old lifestyle. I had been raised by a Southern Baptist preacher, but that was about the extent of my ministry experience.

In my arguments with God, because of my lack of experience, He assured me He would be there every step of the way to guide me. So, after my health took a turn for the worst, I was basically bed ridden, so could do hardly anything other than stay in His Word, in His Spirit and much prayer and meditation. I was lead to the idea, I must return to school and get my Ph. D. in Pastorate ministry to even be able to communicate with pastors in todays culture everything my Lord had been telling me I must share with them. Even then, I found most were totally un-accepting of such a message. Never the less, I pursued my degree at Trinity Bible College and Seminary.

One thing I was shown in such revelations and visions was how our Lord was also just as displeased with the churches in America today, if not more so, as He was with America its self. In fact, He was holding the churches in America today responsible for the condition of our culture. He shared with me how the American church was doing ok until after WW II when all our great theologians began studying the liberal theology of the Germans and began teaching Christ our Lord intellectually verses relationally. He shared with me on many occasions how His only concern was relationship with His creation, especially the pinnacle of His creation, which of course is man. It is all about LOVE, LOVE OF HIM, and LOVE FOR ONE ANOTHER, especially all who are of HIS KINGDOM! HE showed me how the church in America had lost its love and that it had become more about religion and the intellectual reasons for Christ. Those on the outside looking in could not witness this love the preachers were preaching each Sunday morning.

So, my Lord began speaking to me concerning, if we were to take America back to Him, we would first have to take the church in America back to Him. He began sharing with me that there were many among the churches across the land that were indeed true followers of Christ and that He would begin sharing with them some of these same visions and revelations. He then shared with me that we must then unite these true followers into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body of Christ, thus the beginning of the United Missions of Maxima or www.umomaxima.org.

Through this united voice we were to first begin sharing the love that Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways, not just simply preach about it, thus the beginning of Hope Retreats International or www.hoperetreatsinternational.org. I was to organize this united Body of Christ and were to agree to the two greatest commands according to our Lord as well as the last Christ gave to us before returning to the Father. We were to agree to maximize our individuals God given talents, gifts and resources to build up the Kingdom of God on earth as it is in Heaven.

Through this united voice we were to also become an active voice in all branches of government, from our local branch of government, to state and then a united voice to the federal government. Perhaps this is why many churches have remained distant, the old church and state thing? It is really hard to tell why the churches have remained distant, as far as I can tell, every Christian doctrine is all about one Christ, One Lord, one Spirit and one Body of Christ, yet so many I have shared this vision with, once an individual takes this vision to their pastor or church leader, they become silent, though I know for a fact, at first when they read the vision of Maxima by the guidance of the Holy Spirit, they were excited to know God was working within the Christian community to take America back to God.

I was then shown how so many pastors today as well as church leaders are so entrenched in their own denominational beliefs, doctrine and agenda, they could pay very little attention to Gods. It is almost a pastor or church leader cannot make a move without direction from their denomination. I mean, just looking at Maxima from the perspective of a united effort among the Christian community to share the love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in practical ways out into the local community would bring in the un-churched swarming into their flock. After all, Satan and his disciples have their arms wide open welcoming individuals in. The church on the other hand, if a person does not fit a particular denominations prototype they are discouraged at best from coming. Through such a united voice, who knows, we might become the United Way of Christian services out into the community.

I was shown another area where the church was lacking was discipleship. So many within the church today are simply saved, if indeed they really are, by the skin of their teeth. There has been such emphasis on being saved and adding to the numbers of our particular denomination that we are afraid of offending anyone, that we have neglected discipleship. Just a united effort towards discipleship would radically impact the efficiency in affecting a watching world it would be worth the effort. However, I am still amazed at how silent the church in America is towards Maxima.

I asked my Lord; Why do this through me, I mean why me, who am I to convince Your Church of this need of a united voice? There must be many pastors who are more qualified than I am? He shared with me the denomination thing once again, and how the pastors today are more committed to their denomination than they are to Me and My ways, much less to listen and to hear Me. Besides that, He shared with me that the closest thing out in the world today to this organized voice was the Catholic Church; they are the only ones who had the hierarchy already in place to achieve this. I was to begin from scratch!

I believe this is where you come into the equation. It seems to me that my Lord has shared with you some of these same visions and revelations that He has shared with me, from reading several of your articles lately. You are certainly more qualified than I am to make this unified voice a reality. I would think you at least have many who might listen to you. If you have not already done so, this may be an appropriate place for you to go to our site www.umomaxima and drop down to the Vision page and then go to the last page where I show the multiplication of this united voice. With you center of influence we would certainly have a solid foundation to start with if only our Lord would show you the significance of this need. I pray that He does.

It seems to me that we are in total agreement in every way. Another area which I have struggled with is in the area of free enterprise. At one point I felt that free enterprise was not necessarily a Christian approach to governing a society. However, I coming from the secular business world in the film industry, as I struggled with this I had to come to the conclusion as I have seen you have also, that free enterprise is the only economy which works economically. As you aptly point out in one of your articles;

Who Does Jesus Call a Fool? Found at http://www.jamesrobison.net/?q=node/119

Learning to live with the bountiful blessings and prosperity freedom offers will always be a challenge. History reveals that many people, if not most, do not handle it well. This is why God must always be first. Because people so often tragically fail to respond properly to success, do not make the mistake of opposing, resisting, and even beginning to resent the freedom, opportunity, and blessings God offers.

If people do not make wise choices, some government or power will readily impose someone elses will on each of us denying our freedom while ignoring the importance of personal responsibility. When the population refuses to live under the control of God, His Spirit and truth, control will be imposed by those who most often lack both principle and wisdom. We experience judgment for turning from God when excessive government control takes over and our freedom wanes. Abundance and prosperity decreases along with the ability to freely share with others meeting their pressing needs.

As you so adequately point out here, the problem is we in the church in America have simply gotten away from making whom we profess as our Lord our real Lord. Do we even truly believe what we say we believe?

You then make your reference to James 5:2-5 and say;

This farmer who obviously received the benefits of the fertile land and the freedom to produce is typical of our own great, blessed, free, and prosperous nation, the USA. The farmer made the same mistake many are making today forgetting God and, as a result, forgetting others Jesus called him a fool!

Dont miss the truth in this story. The fertile field of opportunity was not the problem. The fruitfulness and abundant harvest and even the wealth it produced were not the problem. The need to expand in order to protect the produce from the harvest and build bigger barns was not the problem. Bigger barns and great gain was not the problem. It was the smallness of his character and his soul caused by the lack of love for God and others that brought him down.

Is this not exactly what I have been shown by the visions and revelations? The very first thing we must do in order to take America back to God, is to first take the churches in America back to God. We must emphasize discipleship once again, and we must truly ask ourselves do we truly believe what we say we believe. There are simply too many within the church in America today who have this same smallness of character, and the reason I have been shown is lack of abandonment of ourselves to the Lordship of Christ, whom we say we believe, so that the Holy Spirit of God may come into us and completely change our hearts.

I have been shown by the Spirit that we must first make the disciples that are already in the churches across America ready to undertake such an organization to embrace those coming into this one voice and one accord, so that they might then be discipled as well.

So, it seems we are in complete agreement that the free enterprise system is indeed a blessing from our God because of our founding Fathers healthy fear of God, and their devotion to our Lord. It also seems we are in agreement over our need for more discipleship. It even appears that you have been shown also how we must rise together in a unified effort, we you continue your discourse with an appeal to your reader;

Let us rise up together in faith and reclaim the land for the glory of God by first giving God the cultivated field of our own lives.1 Corinthians 3:9 says, we are Gods cultivated field Lets be fruitful and multiply, obeying the commandments of the Lord. Pray that God will send more laborers into the fields for they are white unto harvest. This is the day to become more fruitful than ever for the glory of our Father. Let us not give satan one inch of our lives or our land. The farmer was a fool and we will prove to be foolish if we fault the fields and the God who gave the increase, the potential for fruitfulness, freedom and, yes, the free market opportunities we are blessed to have in America. Remember, no government power can better do for us than what God desires to do for and with those who put Him first! We will prove to be fools if we worship what we have rather than the God who is able to do exceedingly abundantly above and beyond anything we imagined!

You even further your discourse in an article entitled Body Armor for the Culture War found at http://jamesrobison.net/?q=node/120 which shows further what I would call a real need for us to organize this unified body of true followers of Christ who have been lead by the Holy Spirit to unite in an all out effort to take this once great nation back to God. In this article you say;

Weve heard for years that were in the middle of a culture war. A culture war, unlike a civil war, is not fought with guns and tanks, but with ideas, words, arguments, media, and education. Unlike ordinary political debates, its a fight over the fundamental principles on which cultures are based.

The first two issuesabortion and religious freedomcome together with the recent U.S. Department of Health and Human Services mandate that organizations, including religious organizations, provide health insurance that covers sterilization, contraception and drugs that induce abortion.

The media has tried to turn this into a debate over contraception, which they portrayincorrectlyas a Catholic issue. In reality, all people of faith, indeed, all Americans have something to lose here. If the federal government can force its citizens to pay for things they find morally abhorrent, then there is nothing the government cant do.

Satan has amassed his army against us! His plan is solid and his organizations are strong, while largely the organized Christian churches across this land remains totally divided in any and everything except in what we say we believe. Do we truly believe what we say we believe? I have been shown emphatically by the Spirit that we must unite into one strong voice and one accord to have any chance what so ever to take America back to God! We must get off our butts and begin to practice what we say we believe. The main point is we must organize this unity, with a governing body of elders as well as professional spokes persons who are activist and not afraid to speak truths to the masses, especially our local governments, then the state and finally our federal governments.

I have now spent the last eleven years attempting this. There have been times when we were able to put together a few hundred individuals at a time, but time after time satan has prevailed. This whole eleven years though I have been back in school trying to receive both a Pd. D to teach what I had done all my life, which is film making on a collegiate level so I didnt have to take funds from the ministry I have been called to live on and a ph. D in Pastorate ministry with emphasis in Nouthetic Biblical counseling. Thus, my time has been constrained.

However, I am certain that I have been lead to these articles of yours by the Holy Spirit of God to approach you concerning you either becoming involved in some way in this unified voice, perhaps even taking over as head of this ministry. You have after all, much more experience in ministry than I, as I have just a completed Masters degree at present, not to mention the years of experience you already had in ministry when I got into ministry. You must also already have a much larger center of influence than I do, thus if done properly, you may already have a strong foundation for this unity.

The point I must make here is the urgency I have been shown by the Holy Spirit of God and the mandate that we must organize this Body of Christ into the one voice and one accord we were meant to be prior to mans laws and denominations dividing the Body.

So, I ask you once again, if you have not already done so, please go to our websites www.umomaxima.org and www.hoperetreatsinternational.org as well as www.maximavisionsproductions.com, as this is a film production company who gives 50% of any profits to this ministry, and also uses the powerful medium of films to share Gods truths.

Check out these sites and please get back to me as soon as possible if for nothing else but to give me constructive advise. I ask that before even beginning to read from any of these sites that you first go to our Lord Jesus in prayer asking Him to lead you through the sites and speak to you what He wants you to get from the sites. It is my prayer that you will be able to hear Gods voice in these sites and that you will then act upon what He shares with you. Perhaps it is time that you take the reins of this unified voice? If that is the case, you have my blessings, I just simply ask that you find a way to take my God given talents, resources and gifts and find a place within the ministry where you and our Lord may use me.

ALL the wonderful LOVE OF CHRIST

Pastor Dr. Randall K. Maxwell

As I have stated, all one has to do is serf the internet to find hundreds of others whom God has been sharing things with that are along the same lines as the United Missions of Maxima. There are several things I am absolutely certain. First and foremost, and I really do not think anyone from the Christian community can disagree; this country is on a downhill slide to hell.

We must unite the true followers of Christ into the one mind and one accord, we were meant to be, speaking as one to first our local government, state and finally the federal government if we are to ever take this once great nation back to God. IN order to do this, we must first take the church in America back to God. We must mentor the individuals the true discipleship lifestyle. And, finally, in order to accomplish all this, as opposed to just preaching week after week about this wonderful Love that Christ our Lord has for a hurting world, we must exhibit it with our very lives.

Witness how you may join this unity of the Body of Christ at www.umomaxima.org and see how we share the love Christ our Lord has for a hurting world in very practical ways at www.hoperetreatsinternational.org. To join this unity of the Body of Christ please go to our yahoo group @ http://groups.yahoo.com/group/intimatemomentwithaprophet and look up the file named Covenant of Maxima. Make copy of document, sign and return to the address below.

Hope Retreats International

208 West Couts Street

Weatherford, Texas 76086

(817) 565-7124

umom2003@yahoo.com

Posted on February 15, 2013 by herthagajg

Name: Kristy Socarras Bigelow, Mitchell, Giana & Leele (Brian, a.k.a. daddy, is missing from the photos on account of his refusal to have pictures taken)
Location: Bonnie Brae, Denver, Colorado
Size: 3,500 square feet, with finished basement
Years lived in: 1 year

The bulk of my visit with Kristy and her amazing family was spent in the entryway. Upon stepping inside, the Colorado sun seemed to collect in the fabulous yellow wallpaper and dance around the silver metallic ginkgo leaves. I halfway expected a tropical breeze when I finally set foot into the living room.
